INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(168,25,'preschool',0,'Understand what a war is and the reason for the Revolutionary war.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(169,25,'preschool',1,'What were the flag designs during the war? Draw or color them one of them.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(170,25,'level1',2,'Create a map of the colonies at the time of the Revolutionary War.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(171,25,'level2',3,'Know what year the Revolutionary War began and why. What year did the war end? Create a timeline of 10 major events in the Revolutionary War.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(172,25,'level3',4,'Include 20 events in your timeline.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(173,25,'level3',5,'Read the Declaration of Independence. Discuss its meaning with an adult. What major events lead up to its writing? Who signed it? When was it written?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(174,25,'level4',6,'Include 25 events in your timeline.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(175,25,'level4',7,'At the end of the war, America had some challenges to face. Read a summary of the Articles of Confederation. How do they differ from the Constitution?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(176,25,'level5',8,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(177,26,'preschool',0,'Understand the basics of how the Amish live.  Try living an Amish lifestyle for one day as much as possible.  Since the Amish do not use electricty, put away all electronic devices.  This means no TV, cell phones, computers, tablets, etc.  Help an adult make your meals from scratch. No prepackaged foods like crackers, fruit snacks, cookies, etc.  Think dishes like roast chicken, mashed potatoes and gravy and corn bread.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(178,26,'preschool',1,'Look at pictures of the Amish and their communities.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(179,26,'level1',2,'Explore how the Amish use technology and the reasons behind their choices.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(180,26,'level2',3,'Read a book or watch a video about the Amish.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(181,26,'level3',4,'Research and create a timeline highlighting key events in Amish history.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(182,26,'level4',5,'Learn about the Amish faith.  Compare and contrast it to other Protestant Christian faiths.  How are they different?  How are they the same?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(183,26,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(184,27,'preschool',0,'Learn the definition of this animal group. What about them classifies them as such?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(185,27,'preschool',1,'Find out as much as you can about the animal group you have chosen in your local environment by reading, observing and talking to others. If your chosen animal group does not live in your community, where is the nearest place that they live naturally?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(186,27,'level1',2,'Be able to identify at least 3 species of your animal group.  You may want to look at things like size, shape, color or other distinguishing marks. Learn about their life cycle, what they eat, how they protect themselves, their calls, and habits.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(187,27,'level2',3,'but identify at least 5 species (If you completed this badge for the same animal group at a different level, you may not use species you have researched in the past.)');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(188,27,'level3',4,'Identify at least 8 species (If you completed this badge for the same animal group at a different level, you may not use species you have researched in the past.)');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(189,27,'level3',5,'If possible, observe your animal category in the wild on at least 3 different occasions. Take notes on their behavior and compare them to what you have learned.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(190,27,'level4',6,'Identify at least 12 species (If you completed this badge for the same animal group at a different level, you may not use species you have researched in the past.)');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(191,27,'level4',7,'If possible, observe your animal category in the wild on at least 5 different occasions.  Take notes on their behavior and compare them to what you have learned.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(192,27,'level5',8,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(193,28,'preschool',0,'Learn what an amusement park is and visit the one you are earning a badge for in person.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(194,28,'level1',1,'Learn the history of your park. Who owns it, (family or corporation)? When did it open? What were the original rides?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(195,28,'level2',2,'Be able to read a map of the park and show that you can navigate to at least 6 different areas.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(196,28,'level3',3,'Learn about the physical science behind one of your favorite rides.  Why is it designed the way it is?  What makes it work?  How is it engineered so that it is safe?  Explain things like acceleration, centripetal force, Newton’s Law of motion, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(197,28,'level4',4,'Find out about careers at the park.  What type of jobs go into creating a theme park?  Choose one job that interests you and find out what type of education you would need for this job?  What type of hours would you work?  What type of pay could you expect?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(198,28,'level5',5,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(199,29,'preschool',0,'Choose an animal that interests you.  Be able to identify it and learn its basic anatomy.  What is a male, female, and baby called?  What is a group of this animal called (a flock, herd, pack, etc.)?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(200,29,'preschool',1,'What does its home look like? A nest? A burrow? A dead tree?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(201,29,'level1',2,'Do PRESCHOOL 1 requirements 1 & 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(202,29,'level1',3,'Make a life cycle chart about your chosen animal. Learn about their babies. How many are born at a time, and are they born live or as eggs?  Learn how big the animal is when it is born and how big it gets. How long do they usually live? Know what they eat and what predators eat them.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(203,29,'level2',4,'Learn where this animal lives (continent, states, countries, etc). Locate the areas on a map or globe and learn what climate and biome it lives in.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(204,29,'level3',5,'Understand the difference between instinct and learned behavior.  Which of your animal’s behaviors are learned and which are instinctual? What instincts does your animal have to help it survive?  Examples might include things like migration or hibernation. What behavior has it learned? Are any of your animal’s behaviors linked to the environment or climate in which it is found? How so? How does it adapt to seasonal changes? Do the animal’s physical characteristics help it in any way?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(205,29,'level4',6,'Find out what associations, foundations, or groups study your animal. How do their research and actions help the animal and our understanding of it?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(206,29,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(207,30,'preschool',0,'Learn to identify at least 5 animals that do not live in your part of the world.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(208,30,'preschool',1,'Create a craft or art project that involves animals from around the world.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(209,30,'level1',2,'Learn to identify at least 10 animals that do not live in your part of the world.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(210,30,'level1',3,'Choose one category of animals (birds, mammals, reptiles, insects, fish, amphibians) and compare how they differ between at least 3 different countries.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(211,30,'level2',4,'Learn to identify at least 25 animals that do not live in your part of the world.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(212,30,'level2',5,'Learn what type of animals live in the following biomes: Desert Rain Forest Ocean Grasslands Deciduous Forest Savanna Tundra A great resource for these requirements is Blue Planet Biomes: http://www.blueplanetbiomes.org/world_biomes.htm (third party website). Please get parent’s permission before browsing this website.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(213,30,'level3',6,'Learn to identify at least 50 animals that do not live in your part of the world.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(214,30,'level3',7,'Choose one animal family and show how it differs around the world. This can be done via essay, booklet, poster, art project, oral presentation, etc. For example, if you chose wildcats, you would need to include the lion, tiger, lynx, cougar, jaguar, snow leopard, etc. There are 36 wildcat species around the world. How do they differ?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(215,30,'level4',8,'Make a list of at least 20 animals around the world that are on the endangered species list. What is being done to help save them?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(216,30,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(217,31,'preschool',0,'What is migration? Why do some animals migrate and others don’t?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(218,31,'preschool',1,'Choose two different animals and learn about their migration journey through your badgerequirements. What do your animals look like?  Why do they migrate?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(219,31,'level1',2,'Learn what times of the year animals migrate. Why are these times significant?  Find out when your chosen animals migrate.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(220,31,'level2',3,'Learn about animal instincts and how they play a role in migration. How do animals knowwhen and where to migrate? Are there any outside forces that contribute to animal instinct when it comes to knowing when to start migrating?  Find out how your chosen animals know when and where to migrate.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(221,31,'level3',4,'Learn about some of the ways that animals prepare for migration. Also, research howsome animals’ bodies change and adapt to handle the stresses of migration.  Find out how your chosen animals prepare for migration.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(222,31,'level4',5,'Research the impact of climate change on migration patterns and discuss potential solutions.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(223,31,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(224,32,'preschool',0,'Understand the importance of animal rescue and why it is essential to help animals in need.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(225,32,'preschool',1,'Learn about the different types of pets commonly found in shelters, including dogs, cats, and small animals.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(226,32,'level1',2,'Learn about different types of animal rescues, such as domestic, wildlife, and farm animal rescue.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(227,32,'level2',3,'Learn how to properly handle and care for a specific animal, including feeding, grooming, and exercise.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(228,32,'level3',4,'Research the importance of pet rescue and adoption, including statistics on pet overpopulation and euthanasia.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(229,32,'level4',5,'Research the challenges faced by animal shelters and rescues, including funding and resource limitations.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(230,32,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(231,33,'preschool',0,'What are animal tracks? Be able to recognize a set of tracks on a photograph or in the ground.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(232,33,'preschool',1,'Be able to tell what kind of ground you can find tracks on. (E.g. Do you think you will find tracks in the grass? Do you think you will find any animal tracks on the pavement? In the mud at the ditch/creek?) Level 1: Do four requirements including the twos tarred *');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(233,33,'preschool',2,'Do Preschool 1 & 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(234,33,'preschool',3,'Identify at least 3 animal tracks. Be able to identify deer and raccoon tracks.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(235,33,'level2',4,'Be able to identify 5 different tracks.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(236,33,'level2',5,'Find an animal track outside, and then go back inside and research it using an encyclopedia, nature guide, or internet if you don’t recognize it.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(237,33,'level3',6,'Be able to identify 10 different tracks.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(238,33,'level3',7,'Learn about molds, and cast a mold of an animal track.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(239,33,'level4',8,'Explain the concept of gaits and how they can help in determining an animal’s speed and behavior based on the tracks found.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(240,33,'level5',9,'Do Level 4 requirement #1.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(241,33,'level5',10,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(242,34,'preschool',0,'Watch 3 different animated TV shows or movies from 3 different producers.  Which animation style did you like best and why?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(243,34,'preschool',1,'In animation, everyday objects like cars or toys can come to life and behave like people.   Discuss what make believe is and then watch an animated show and identify characters and other animations than are not real.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(244,34,'level1',2,'Watch one of the earliest animated characters such as Felix the Cat or Steamboat Willie.  How do they differ from animations you see today?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(245,34,'level2',3,'Make a flip book with at least 20 pages.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(246,34,'level3',4,'Animation is commonly used in commercials, promotional videos, and digital advertisements to capture attention, explain products or services, and convey brand messages in a creative and engaging way.  As you watch TV or surf the internet, pay attention to animation in advertising.  How does animation convey the message better than static images or text?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(247,34,'level4',5,'Learn the history of animation and create a timeline with at least 15 significant milestones.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(248,34,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(249,35,'preschool',0,'Read or have read to you the first Anne of Green Gables book. At the preschool level, an abridged version is fine.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(250,35,'level1',1,'Read or have read to you the complete and unabridged Anne of Green Gables.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(251,35,'level1',2,'Learn where Prince Edward Island is on a map.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(252,35,'level2',3,'Read at least two books in the Anne of Green Gables series.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(253,35,'level2',4,'Create a chart listing the main characters from Anne of Green Gables, including characters from later books, like Katherine. Which ones are your favorites?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(254,35,'level3',5,'Read at least four books in the Anne of Green Gables series.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(255,35,'level3',6,'Create a detailed timeline of Anne Shirley’s life, highlighting important events and milestones mentioned throughout the series. Include at least 25 events.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(256,35,'level4',7,'Read the entire Anne of Green Gables book series.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(257,35,'level4',8,'Anne was adopted from an orphanage. Learn about real-life orphanages, foster care, and other forms of care for orphaned or abused children. How have things changed since Anne’s time? How are they similar?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(258,35,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(259,36,'preschool',0,'Learn what bullying means.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(260,36,'preschool',1,'Practice sharing with your friends and learn to wait your turn.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(261,36,'level1',2,'Role play bullying scenarios and ways to deal with bullying. Make a list of adults you can go to if you are the victim of bullying. Examples might include parents, teachers, bus drivers, family members, or police.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(262,36,'level2',3,'Cyber bullying has become an epidemic. A simple mean comment, or picture, sent to one person, can now become viral almost instantly. Anything posted online, no matter how private you think it is, always has the potential to become publicly distributed. Make a list of ways that cyberbullying can occur. Write an anti-bullying pledge to never post, or repost, an unkind word or picture online, even through a private email or text. Get as many friends as possible to sign it.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(263,36,'level3',4,'Find out the statistics for bullying at your age level. How often does it occur? What type of bullying is most common? Discuss what role you can play to help eliminate bullying.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(264,36,'level4',5,'Find out what anti-bullying legislature has passed both federally, and in your own state. What specific forms of bullying do the laws address? What are the punishments?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(265,36,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(268,38,'preschool',0,'Find the Appalachian Trail on a map. What states does it go through?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(269,38,'preschool',1,'Earn the Leave No Trace and Hiking badges at your level.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(270,38,'level1',2,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(271,38,'level1',3,'How many miles is the Appalachian Trail? Who takes care of the trail? Why was it built and when? How is it marked?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(272,38,'level2',4,'What National Parks and National Forests does the trail go through? What is a thru-hiker? A day hiker? A section hiker? What are 5 other long distance trails in the U.S.?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(273,38,'level3',5,'Learn about thru hiking: What is a north bounder? A south bounder? A flip-flop hiker? When do hikers generally start? What are the pros and cons of each style? How many people thru hike each year? How long does it take? Who are the oldest and youngest thru hikers?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(274,38,'level4',6,'Make a list of what you think a thru-hiker would carry and then check it with another source. How do hikers minimize their pack weights? What is a normal pack weight?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(275,38,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(276,39,'preschool',0,'Sample and identify at least 2 different types of apples.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(277,39,'preschool',1,'Learn the life cycle of an apple (seed, seedling, tree, flower, fruit, seed….).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(278,39,'level1',2,'Sample and identify at least 3 different types of apples.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(279,39,'level1',3,'Learn about Johnny Appleseed.  What was his real name? When did he live?  Why did he become a legend?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(280,39,'level2',4,'Sample and identify at least 4 different types of apples.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(281,39,'level2',5,'Find out where apples are typically grown and in what season. Locate major apple growing regions on a map. Do they specialize in a particular type of apple, or all apples in general?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(282,39,'level3',6,'Sample and identify at least 5 different types of apples.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(283,39,'level3',7,'Find out what types of vitamins and minerals are in apples. How many grams of fiber does a typical apple have? What health benefits do these provide your body?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(284,39,'level4',8,'Sample and identify at least 6 different types of apples.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(285,39,'level4',9,'Make at least 3 recipes using apples. If you choose to use optional requirements that involve recipes, these must be done in addition to the three mentioned in this requirement.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(286,39,'level5',10,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(287,40,'preschool',0,'Understand what an aquarium is.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(288,40,'preschool',1,'What types of fish and sea creatures live in an aquarium? Name at least 5 and understand what they are.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(289,40,'level1',2,'Visit an aquarium or watch a documentary about an aquarium.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(290,40,'level2',3,'Learn about five different exhibits from your chosen aquarium.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(291,40,'level3',4,'Learn about the following systems in an aquarium: filtration, lighting, temperature control, water and air pumps, water treatment and salt mix.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(292,40,'level4',5,'Learn about the history and architecture of this aquarium. When did it open? Where do they get their fish and sea creatures?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(293,40,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(294,41,'level1',0,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(295,41,'level1',1,'What does it mean to loot an archaeological site? Why is this bad? What are other dangers to archaeological sites?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(296,41,'level2',2,'What are the phases of an archaeological excavation?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(297,41,'level3',3,'Learn about pioneer archaeologists. Create a timeline of 10 important archaeological events.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(298,41,'level4',4,'What remote sensing instruments are used in archaeology and what do they do?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(299,41,'level5',5,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(300,42,'preschool',0,'Learn the general safety rules for archery including: How and when to retrieve arrows How to carry arrows Where to stand while others are shooting Where to point your arrow What the safety zones are at an archery range. Know and follow the archery range whistle commands. What arm guards and finger tabs are and why you should wear them.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(301,42,'preschool',1,'Practice your archery safety rules with a toy bow and arrow.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(302,42,'level1',2,'Level 1 may use a toy bow or a real one that is age appropriate under the supervision of a trained adult.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(303,42,'level1',3,'Watch an archery tournament. This can be in person, on TV, or online with the permission of your parent.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(304,42,'level2',4,'Level 2 and above should be using real bows that are age and size appropriate.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(305,42,'level2',5,'Demonstrate good archery shooting techniques including: Stance Nocking the arrow Establish the bow Draw Aim Release Follow-through Retrieve arrows');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(306,42,'level3',6,'Know your local and state laws for owning and using archery tackle.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(307,42,'level3',7,'Explain how to properly store and care for archery equipment including bows, arrows, tabs, arm guards, shooting gloves, and quivers.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(308,42,'level4',8,'Demonstrate how to judge good bows and arrows identify the parts of each.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(309,42,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(310,43,'preschool',0,'What is architecture? What makes it an art? What does an architect do?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(311,43,'preschool',1,'Find pictures of the buildings from 3 different ancient civilizations. What makes their buildings different? Level 1: Do four activities including the one starred *');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(312,43,'preschool',2,'Why would buildings look different depending on where/when it was built?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(313,43,'preschool',3,'Find some architect’s drawings or models to observe. These can be in a public location as historic pieces or future plans OR you can visit the office of an architect to see a current project.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(314,43,'level2',4,'What could science and math have to do with architecture?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(315,43,'level2',5,'Read at least two well-illustrated books about three ancient civilizations. Write a description of what makes the architecture different for each of the civilizations.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(316,43,'level3',6,'Read about four ancient civilizations. Try to identify the two most famous structures of each civilization and write out why they are famous. What makes the styles different?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(317,43,'level3',7,'Read about architecture in an encyclopedia. What do you find most interesting about architecture? Why can’t architects usually build their own designs? What kind of things do you think an architect would need to study in school?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(318,43,'level4',8,'If you did this badge earlier, choose civilizations you did not study previously. Identify the characteristics of the ancient buildings that make them unique to that civilization. Find good maps that show where the civilizations were located. Present pictures of buildings of at least one of the civilizations to your family, friends, club, or troop & point out the unique features.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(319,43,'level4',9,'Draw your own version of the architect’s drawings or models that you saw for Level 1 requirement #2. Pretend something needs to be changed on the project, such as making the building twice as big or half as big as the real one and show how you would do that.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(320,43,'level5',10,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(321,44,'preschool',0,'Understand what the Army is and what their role is in the military.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(322,44,'level1',1,'Understand what the Army is and what their role is in the military.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(323,44,'level1',2,'Learn the history of the U.S. Army and how it began, as well as its mission today.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(324,44,'level2',3,'Describe the different ways of being in the Army Active Duty, Reserve, and National Guard. How do they differ? How are they the same?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(325,44,'level3',4,'Discuss the contributions the U.S. Army has made to our country or write an essay about these contributions.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(326,44,'level4',5,'Visit an Army recruiter. Find out how to enlist in the Army or be commissioned as an Army officer. What jobs are available? What training is provided? How long must you enlist for? What are the benefits of joining the military? What are the drawbacks? How does your education and background affect your salary in the Army?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(327,44,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(328,45,'preschool',0,'Learn the difference between line, color, shape and texture.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(329,45,'preschool',1,'Make four pieces of art using four different techniques (painting, printing, drawing, sculpting) or four different media (watercolors, pencils, ink, clay).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(330,45,'level1',2,'Make a piece of art that emphasizes one of the elements of art (line, color, space, form, shape, texture, value).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(331,45,'level2',3,'plus find a picture of a piece of art that emphasizes a second element of art.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(332,45,'level2',4,'Make a piece of art that emphasizes one of the principles of art (emphasis, balance, harmony, variety, proportion, rhythm, movement, unity).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(333,45,'level3',5,'Find pictures that emphasize at least 3 elements of art and 3 principles of art.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(334,45,'level3',6,'Choose a subject (pine trees, poodles or daisies for example) and make two pieces of art in your choice of either two different media or two different styles.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(335,45,'level4',7,'Read or watch a biography or documentary on an artist.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(336,45,'level5',8,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(337,46,'preschool',0,'Learn how art has changed through time. Look through an art history book that has pictures of art work from cave walls in primitive civilizations through to the present day. Which are your favorite art works?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(338,46,'preschool',1,'Find 3 famous pieces of artwork (it may be a painting, sculpture, etc) and learn who created them, where and when.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(339,46,'level1',2,'Learn the following chief periods of art history and one general characteristic of each era: Prehistoric & Primitive Ancient civilizations — Egyptian, Greek & Roman. Medieval Renaissance Romantic Modern');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(340,46,'level2',3,'Using prints, flashcards, or photos in a book, be able to identify by name and artist, 10 different world-famous pieces of art from at least two different eras of art history. This requirement may be repeated with different works of art.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(341,46,'level3',4,'Identify 15 pieces of art.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(342,46,'level3',5,'Try to copy a famous piece of art. Be sure to use paint, ink, charcoal or pencils that will look the closest to what the artist used.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(343,46,'level4',6,'Identify 20 pieces of art.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(344,46,'level4',7,'List as many types of visual art as you can. Be sure you know the following vocabulary: sculpture, figurine, statue, mobile, 3-D, canvas, portrait, mural, tapestry.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(345,46,'level5',8,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(346,47,'preschool',0,'Go outside and create a piece of artwork from what you see.  You might draw a tree or flower, sculpt an animal, paint a rainbow or photograph a bug.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(347,47,'preschool',1,'Create a piece of art using something you find in nature.  Make sure to follow no trace rules if you are on public land.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(348,47,'level1',2,'Create a mosaic using small sticks, rocks, fallen leaves, acorns or other small items from nature you find on the ground.  Glue them onto cardboard or simply layout your design in the dirt or grass if you are on public land and need to leave no trace when you leave.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(349,47,'level2',3,'Go out in nature and draw, paint or photograph the natural landscape you see.  This might be a view of a waterfall, the mountains, a river, or a forest.  Pay attention to artistic details such as lighting and composition.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(350,47,'level3',4,'Learn about the benefits of spending time in nature.  How does creating art in nature improve your health?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(351,47,'level4',5,'Do Level 3requirements 1 & 2');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(352,47,'level4',6,'Learn what Ephemeral Art is and create a piece outdoors in nature.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(353,47,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(354,48,'preschool',0,'What is art?  What is imagination and creativity? Is it still art if it isn’t pretty?  Look at some examples of your specific type of art.  Discuss thoughts or feelings the art may create for you or others.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(355,48,'preschool',1,'Create your specific type of art.  If creating it isn’t practicable or applicable, draw or otherwise model  it.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(356,48,'level1',2,'What are some of the materials often used to create your art?  What are the tools often used?Learn the basic process for creating your art.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(357,48,'level2',3,'Learn the history of your specific art.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(358,48,'level3',4,'Name three artists and study least one piece each of their artwork.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(359,48,'level4',5,'Does your art have subcategories?  What are the differences between the categories?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(360,48,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to create your specific art, and help them complete a project.  You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(361,49,'preschool',0,'Understand what artificial intelligence is and why it is useful.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(362,49,'preschool',1,'Discuss the types of things that humans can do that AI cannot, and that AI can do that humans cannot.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(363,49,'level1',2,'Discuss simple ways AI is used such as voice assistants, product recommendations, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(364,49,'level1',3,'Understand basic terms related to AI: artificial intelligence, machine learning, deep learning, training data');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(365,49,'level2',4,'Do a guided AI programming activity (such as an Hour of Code).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(366,49,'level3',5,'Research the history of AI and create a timeline highlighting key milestones and breakthroughs in the field.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(367,49,'level4',6,'Discuss the ethical delimmas presented by AI, including privacy, bias, and job displacement.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(368,49,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(371,51,'preschool',0,'What is astronomy? What sort of things are out in space that we can study (such as stars, planets, meteors, asteroids etc)? Look at pictures of them. What is the Milky Way and can you see it?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(372,51,'preschool',1,'Learn what safety precautions to take when making observations at night. What is the proper clothing for observing at night when it is cold? When it is warm? How can you safely observe the sun, objects near the sun, and the moon? Why is it dangerous if you do it incorrectly? Go outside with an adult and look at the stars.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(373,51,'level1',2,'Learn what the following things are: Star Planet Atmosphere Moon Galaxy Solar system.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(374,51,'level1',3,'Be able to name the 8 major planets and the 5 dwarf planets in our solar system. Know their position from the sun. Which are the 3 most visible?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(375,51,'level2',4,'Add to the list: Orbit Gravity Comet Asteroid Meteorite Meteor Universe.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(376,51,'level2',5,'Learn to identify 5 constellations in the night sky.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(377,51,'level3',6,'Add the following to the list: Eclipse Equinox Solstice Star map Asteroid belt Satellite (natural and man-made) Dwarf planet.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(378,51,'level3',7,'Identify at least 10 constellations in the night sky.  Be able to identify the North Star. Explain first aid for injuries or illnesses that may occur during observation such as bites and stings, dehydration, damage to your eyes, or heat and cold reactions.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(379,51,'level4',8,'Add to the list: Black hole Red giant White dwarf Kuiper Belt Hypernova Supernova Mass Gravitational force.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(380,51,'level4',9,'Identify at least 12 constellations, at least 3 of which are in the zodiac. Be able to identify the North Star.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(381,51,'level5',10,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(382,52,'preschool',0,'Discuss with a parent or other adult what attentiveness means. How can you be attentive with your five senses? In your mind? With your posture? What are the benefits to being attentive?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(383,52,'level1',1,'Perform an “Attentiveness check” once a day for a week. Have an adult check off each time you perform this well. In this attentiveness check you will: Choose an opportunity such as when your parent or teacher is about to give you instruction on how to do something and ask that person if you can do an “attentiveness check”. Listen carefully and watch closely to what is being said/done. Correctly repeat/demonstrate back what you were told/shown.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(384,52,'level2',2,'Name a career that requires your full attention and describe it. In your written report, include how they are able to pay attention and what can happen if that person is not paying attention as they should.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(385,52,'level3',3,'Demonstrate your ability to observe things around you. In times of war, crime, and emergencies, good observation skills become critical.  To pass this requirement you do not need to have a perfect memory of everything you see.  You DO need to understand the importance of observing things around you and how these details may be important in an emergency. First, walk ¼ mile and try to remember how many cars you saw, what color they were, what type, where were they parked, etc. Walk it again and pay attention to the people you see.  Were they male or female, what were they wearing how old were they, how tall, what color hair did they have, what color eyes, etc. Walk it a third time and observe the buildings. How many stories were they, how many doors and windows did each one have, what color was the main building, what color was the trim, did they pitched roofs or flat, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(386,52,'level4',4,'Do Level 3 requirements #1 & 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(387,52,'level4',5,'Watch a foreign movie in which you must read subtitles. Write a summary of the main characters and the plot of the story. What did you like about it? Dislike? How was it different from American movies?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(388,52,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(389,53,'preschool',0,'Learn what the Aurora borealis, or northern lights, are. Look at pictures of the lights in the sky.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(390,53,'preschool',1,'Draw or paint a picture of the Northern Lights.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(391,53,'level1',2,'Learn a myth or story related to the Northern Lights.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(392,53,'level2',3,'Identify and explain the colors of the aurora and what gases cause them.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(393,53,'level3',4,'Explain what causes the aurora borealis and how solar wind interacts with Earth’s magnetosphere. Create a simple diagram of the process.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(394,53,'level4',5,'Explore how the aurora impacts modern technology, such as GPS and satellites.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(395,53,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(396,54,'preschool',0,'Understand that everyone has different abilities. Learn what autism is and how it can affect people’s behavior.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(397,54,'level1',1,'Learn about sensory overload. For example, try turning on some music very loud and then try to read a book, or complete a difficult project. Discuss your experience and how it relates to someone with autism.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(398,54,'level2',2,'Learn about the most common symptoms of autism.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(399,54,'level3',3,'Learn about when autism was first diagnosed and why it is so puzzling to doctors. Find out how many children are diagnosed with autism each year.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(400,54,'level4',4,'Learn about teaching methods and treatments for autism.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(401,54,'level5',5,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(402,55,'preschool',0,'What is automotive maintenance? Be able to explain to someone how caring for your vehicle is very important to make sure that it is safe to drive.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(403,55,'preschool',1,'Which parts of the car need to be checked frequently to make sure that it is safe to drive?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(404,55,'level1',2,'Discuss with an adult what hazards you may encounter when checking or performing maintenance on a vehicle. What can you do to maintain your safety while checking and maintaining a vehicle?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(405,55,'level1',3,'Perform a maintenance check on a vehicle with the help of an adult: Make sure no indicator lights are on in the dash. Make sure the headlights, tail lights, reverse lights, brake lights, windshield wipers, and horn are all working properly. If it applies in your state, be sure the registration and inspection are current. How often should you perform this check?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(406,55,'level2',4,'Learn and demonstrate how to check the oil in a vehicle.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(407,55,'level3',5,'Learn and demonstrate how to check the air pressure in a vehicles tires as well as how to add air when needed. Why is maintaining proper air pressure important to the life of your vehicle’s tires? Locate and check the air filter on a vehicle. Learn how to replace the air filter. Why is it necessary to have an air filter? How often should it be replaced?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(408,55,'level4',6,'Learn and demonstrate how to change a tire on a vehicle. How long do tires typically last? What signs should you look for that tires need to be replaced?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(409,55,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(410,56,'preschool',0,'Define “aircraft.” Describe at least three different types of aircraft and be able to recognize them from pictures. Examples might include propeller planes, jets, helicopters, gliders, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(411,56,'preschool',1,'Make a paper airplane with the help of an adult and see how well you can fly it.  Make a change to your plane such as which way your flaps bend and see how it affects the plane’s flight.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(412,56,'level1',2,'Using a diagram or model airplane, identify the following parts of an aircraft and know what each are for: Fuselage Cockpit Propeller Wings Flaps Ailerons Rudder Horizontal stabilizer Elevator Landing gear.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(413,56,'level2',3,'Make at least two different types of paper airplane.  How do they differ?  Which one flies better?  Why?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(414,56,'level2',4,'Explain, using a diagram or a model airplane, the forces that act on an airplane in flight.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(415,56,'level3',5,'Explain the differences in how piston, turboprop, and jet engines operate.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(416,56,'level4',6,'Obtain and learn how to read an aeronautical chart. Measure a true course on the chart.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(417,56,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(418,57,'preschool',0,'Learn about the development of a baby before it is born. Look at pictures of one inside its mother’s womb.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(419,57,'preschool',1,'Learn how to change a baby’s diaper. You can practice either with a real baby or a baby doll.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(420,57,'level1',2,'Find out what the top baby names were for last year. How did they differ from the most popular names 50 years ago?  Look through a baby name book and choose names you like. Find out what they mean. What does your own name mean?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(421,57,'level2',3,'Learn about the development of babies after they are born, such as average height and weight at different ages, average age of their first tooth, motor development stages, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(422,57,'level3',4,'Babies drink either breast milk or formula. Research both and find the pros and cons of each.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(423,57,'level4',5,'Learn about the different types of births, such as natural birth, C-section, stillbirth, etc. Write a short summary on each one that you learn about.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(424,57,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(425,59,'preschool',0,'What is backpacking? How is it different from other kinds of camping?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(426,59,'preschool',1,'Earn the Wilderness Survival and Hiking badges at your level.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(427,59,'level1',2,'Learn safety rules when backpacking that are appropriate to your age and skill level.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(428,59,'level1',3,'Make a list of at least ten places to go backpacking. A minimum of three must be in your state. Include how long the trail is and what kind of terrain it has.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(429,59,'level2',4,'Help plan and go on a backpacking trip of at least one night and 10 miles. Your plan should include a complete packing list. Keep a journal during your trip. Level 3: Do six requirements including theÂ two starred *');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(430,59,'level2',5,'For Level 2 requirement 2, those in Level 3 must plan and go on a backpacking trip of at least 2 nights and 17 miles. Your plan should include a complete packing list as well as meal planning. Your journal should include the time while you plan your trip.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(431,59,'level2',6,'Explain the importance of water during a backpacking trip. How much water would you need for each day that water is not available on the trail? How would you carry it with you? If water is available on the trail, list three ways you could purify it so it is safe to drink. Demonstrate at least one of those ways.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(432,59,'level4',7,'For Level 2 requirement 2, those in Level 4 must plan and go on a backpacking trip of at least 3 nights and 25 miles. Your plan should include a map of your trip, description of the trail, where you will camp at night, a budget, and a list of all equipment and food you will bring. Your journal should also include reflections after you return from your trip.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(433,59,'level4',8,'Learn the correct ways of handling human and other wastes while on a backpacking trip. Describe the importance of personal cleanliness while on a backpacking trip. What are some ways you could maintain personal cleanliness while in the wilderness?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(434,59,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(435,60,'preschool',0,'What kinds of wild animals live around your house? Discuss with your family the different kinds of animals you have seen in your yard or neighborhood.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(436,60,'preschool',1,'How do you think these animals find food in the winter?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(437,60,'level1',2,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(438,60,'level1',3,'What can people do to help these animals find food in the winter without making them dependent on you?  Learn about the food chain and make a chart of the food chain in your backyard.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(439,60,'level2',4,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(440,60,'level2',5,'Make a chart of the kinds of animals that you see in your yard for one week.   Record the following types of information:  kind of animal, activity (digging, running, being still…), number of times you saw it per day using tally marks, etc. Show your chart to your family, friends, or other group.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(441,60,'level3',6,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(442,60,'level3',7,'What effect does the animal’s search for food have on your yard? Where do the animals live?  How does that affect their food supply? Write a short report addressing these topics.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(443,60,'level4',8,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(444,60,'level4',9,'Research at least five types of wildlife in your area using at least three different types of sources (books, Internet, documentaries, agencies, associations, etc.)  Create a chart showing a minimum of five facts about each animal (e.g. their life cycle and age span, what they eat, where they live, what family of animals they are part of, how they care for their young, etc.) Show this chart to your family, friends, or other group.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(445,60,'level5',10,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(446,60,'level5',11,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(447,61,'preschool',0,'Spend at least one night outside in your backyard, or in a friend’s.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(448,61,'preschool',1,'Take a look at the night sky and learn about what you see: stars, moon, any night creatures flying?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(449,61,'level1',2,'Star gaze and learn to identify at least one constellation.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(450,61,'level2',3,'but identify at least two constellations.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(451,61,'level2',4,'Learn to roll your own sleeping bag or bedroll. You can even have a sleeping bag rolling relay if you wish. Divide into two teams and place a rolled sleeping bag 20’ in front of each team. One at a time, a team member runs up to the bag, unrolls it and then tightly re-rolls it, tying it appropriately. They then run back and tag the next team member. Continue until all team members have successfully rolled the sleeping bag. The first team to finish wins.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(452,61,'level3',5,'but learn to identify three constellations');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(453,61,'level3',6,'Make a nature collage of things from your backyard, or make a nature bracelet or other craft. To make a bracelet, make a circle of duct tape around your wrist with the sticky side facing out. Stick acorn caps, leaves, small twigs or pebbles to the tape to create a bracelet.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(454,61,'level4',7,'Do Level 3 requirements # 1 & 2, but identify four constellations.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(455,61,'level4',8,'Learn to identify the all the types of trees in your backyard. Do a bark rubbing and leaf rubbing of each and make a tree identification booklet.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(456,61,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(457,62,'level1',0,'Research your topic and come up with a minimum of 7 optional requirements appropriate for each level (many requirements are appropriate for more than one level.). You will need to talk to someone knowledgeable in your subject, research it online (with a parent’ s permission), or go to the library. Following are some ideas to get you started. Knowledge of the subject History of the subject Skills necessary Careers in this area Fun activities to help learn the subject (crafts, songs, games, recipes etc.) Service Projects Ask a parent or club leader for help. When you are finished, turn in your badge to your leader for approval.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(458,62,'level1',1,'When you’re done writing your badge, write a short paragraph on what you learned, who helped you, how you got your idea, and what badge you might want to make next. If you would like to share your experience with others, email a copy to:  kerry@curiosityuntamed.com or send a copy to Curiosity Untamed 20845 Gregory Lane, Redding, CA 96003');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(459,62,'level2',2,'Some badges are on general topics and others are more specific. Look over the badge list, and make a list of some that you like. Then do one of the following: Look and see if the badges have anything in common. If so, is there a general badge you could write on the subject? (For example cross stitch, embroidery and hand sewing could be combined into a Stitchery Badge) Find a general badge such as History that could be broken down into more specific badges such as ancient Egypt, American History, or World History. How many of these badges can you find?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(460,62,'level3',3,'Design what your badge will look like.  Send it to us via email or snail mail. While we do not guarantee we will use the all designs submitted, we will consider all artwork before making our final decision. Keep in mind that the badge will be less than 1” when printed, so keep designs simple.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(461,62,'level4',4,'Come up with an additional 7 requirements for a total of 16 requirements for your badge.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(462,62,'level5',5,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(463,63,'preschool',0,'Learn basic kitchen safety when baking. Some examples of common kitchen safety rules are: Get permission from an adult before you use the kitchen. Always using oven mitts or potholders when opening oven doors, using the range, and handling baking pans or cookie sheets. Children at least through age 10 should be supervised by an adult when they use knives. Make sure knives are properly sharpened; a dull knife is more dangerous than a sharp one. To prevent falls, if you can’t comfortably reach the countertop or kitchen table, have a sturdy stool or booster seat available. Tie your hair back so that it does not get in the food or trapped in a mixer. Wear close-fitting sleeves that won’t accidentally catch fire, get into your batter, or stuck in a mixer. Wash your hands with soap and water before beginning. Do not spread germs by licking your fingers or cooking utensils. Raw egg can give you salmonella poisoning so do not eat raw cookie or cake batter. Turn pot handles to the back of the stove to avoid accidental spills.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(464,63,'preschool',1,'Learn what the following baking terms mean and understand basic baking measurements: Bake Mix Grease Beat Batter Lukewarm');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(465,63,'level1',2,'Add the following terms & basic baking measurements: Fold Combine Knead Drizzle Cream Dough Pack Sift Whip Teaspoon Tablespoon Cup 1/2 cup 1/4 cup 1/3 cup');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(466,63,'level2',3,'Bake a cake using both from scratch and with a mix. Which did you like better? Which is healthier for you?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(467,63,'level3',4,'Make a yeast bread from scratch.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(468,63,'level4',5,'Bake a double crusted pie from scratch.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(469,63,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(470,64,'preschool',0,'Learn about what type of balloons are used in balloon art. What is the difference between art made with round balloons and art made with long thin balloons? Look at pictures of both types of art.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(471,64,'preschool',1,'Learn how to blow up a balloon and have an adult help you tie it in a knot. Learn to use a small balloon pump the help of an adult.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(472,64,'level1',2,'Learn to make a simple twisted balloon art project such as a sword, dog, or flower.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(473,64,'level2',3,'Demonstrate your ability to blow up and tie off your own balloons. Make at least 3 different twisted balloon art pieces using a minimum of three different twist techniques. (tulip/apple twists, wings, legs, etc.)');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(474,64,'level3',4,'Learn about 2 different balloon artists. What type of balloon art do they do? What types of occasions have they designed for? What do their pieces usually sell for? Where do they live?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(475,64,'level4',5,'Learn about the history of balloons. How have balloons evolved throughout history? What have they been used for?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(476,64,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(477,65,'preschool',0,'What is a bandana?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(478,65,'level1',1,'Learn the history of bandanas. They’re older than you might expect! Which country uses the bandana as part of its national costume?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(479,65,'level2',2,'Research the first original bandana designed in the US and who designed it.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(480,65,'level3',3,'Research different types of bandanas. What are souvenir bandanas? Political or campaign bandanas? Children’s bandanas? Fundraising bandanas? Find examples of each.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(481,65,'level4',4,'Explain the safety risks involved in wearing a specific color of bandana in regards to gangs in urban areas. What colors are used by what groups and where?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(482,65,'level5',5,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(483,66,'preschool',0,'Know what money is and what it is used for.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(484,66,'preschool',1,'Understand what a bank is and why they are important.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(485,66,'level1',2,'Visit a bank and take a tour if possible.  Find out what the following items are:  Teller, safety deposit boxes, ATM.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(486,66,'level2',3,'What is a deposit? What is a withdrawal? What does it mean to debit or credit an account?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(487,66,'level3',4,'Understand the difference between online banking and in-person banking.  What are the pros and cons of each?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(488,66,'level4',5,'Know what the FDIC is and what its role is in banking.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(489,66,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(490,67,'preschool',0,'Know who Barbie is. Look at three different types of Barbie dolls, such as Original Barbie, Storybook Barbie, Cultural Barbie, etc. Which one is your favorite and why?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(491,67,'level1',1,'Design your own Barbie outfit using colored pencils, markers, paint, etc. What accessories would you make for her? What colors would you choose? If possible, with a parent’s help, create the outfit and put it on your Barbie.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(492,67,'level2',2,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(493,67,'level2',3,'Learn the history of Barbie. When was she first created? How did the very first Barbie look and how has she evolved today? Research the different types of Barbies on the market today, and how her hair color, body type, fashion sense, interests, etc. has changed over the decades. Create a timeline with at least 15 – 20 items.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(494,67,'level3',4,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(495,67,'level3',5,'How many different Barbies have been made? How many outfits has she had? How much does the average new outfit cost? How many sets of furniture have been made for her? What is the average price of the furniture for one room? With parental permission, investigate the current price for old Barbies on e-Bay.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(496,67,'level4',6,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(497,67,'level4',7,'What country(ies) make Barbie and her extras? Try to find out where the most extensive Barbie collections are located. Find out if anyone has actually made money buying Barbies and saving them to sell later. Does anyone have a business sewing extra clothes (non-brand) for Barbies? Where can you find patterns for Barbie clothes and furniture?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(498,67,'level5',8,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(499,67,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(502,69,'preschool',0,'Learn what a battery is and find things around your house that use batteries (flashlight, toy, remote, etc.).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(503,69,'preschool',1,'Learn safety rules for interacting with batteries and battery powered devices.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(504,69,'level1',2,'Try placing batteries into a device (like a flashlight) the right way, following the + and – symbols. Learn why direction matters.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(505,69,'level2',3,'Learn five vocabulary words related to battery power such as circuit, current, voltage, electrolyte, and terminal');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(506,69,'level3',4,'Learn about the history of battery power. Who invented the first battery? How have batteries changed over time?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(507,69,'level4',5,'Compare different types of batteries (alkaline, lithium-ion, lead-acid, nickel-metal hydride (NiMH) etc.) What are the pros and cons of each?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(508,69,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead. Optional Requirements');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(509,70,'preschool',0,'Understand what a battle is and why countries engage in them.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(510,70,'preschool',1,'Learn what strategy means and play a simple strategy game like Tic Tac Toe.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(511,70,'level1',2,'Study how terrain and geography influence battle strategy. Present an example of a battle where terrain was crucial to the outcome.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(512,70,'level2',3,'Learn about different types of warfare (e.g., guerrilla, conventional, cyber, asymmetric). Explain the strategic differences between two of them.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(513,70,'level3',4,'Study three famous military strategists (e.g., Sun Tzu, Napoleon, Clausewitz). Discuss their contributions to battle strategy.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(514,70,'level4',5,'Analyze a famous historical battle. Identify the strategy used by both sides and its impact on the outcome.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(515,70,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(516,72,'preschool',0,'Know basic water safety rules. Some basic water safety rules include: The best way to stay safe in the water is to learn to swim. Know what the depth markers, buoys, and flags mean in lakes or oceans. Test the water temperature before you plunge in. Cold water can shock your body and make your blood pressure and heart rate go up. You might accidentally open your mouth to yell and accidentally breathe in some water. Cold water can also slow your muscles, making it hard to swim.  Always obey all water rules. Never swim without a buddy. Never dive into shallow or murky water. Never dive into water with submerged obstacles such as rocks or trees. Never swim without an adult present. Swim at a depth that is safe for you. If you’re just learning to swim, stay near the shore. If you swim in an ocean, pond, lake, or river the fish swimming around won’t hurt you. They may hide jagged rocks, broken bottles, or trash however. Wear something to protect your feet. Also, watch out for mud, weeds, kelp, and grass, which can trap even a good swimmer. If you panic and try to yank yourself free, you may get even more tangled. Instead, shake and pull your arms an legs slowly to work yourself loose or call for an adult’s help. Don’t chew gum or eat while you swim — you could choke. Stop swimming or boating as soon as you see or hear a storm. Remember, lightning is electricity — electricity and water are a dangerous combination. If you find yourself in trouble and someone comes to rescue you in deep water, remain calm and do not grab a hold of your rescuer. If you interfere with your rescuer you can both drown. Stay calm and let them “tow” you to safety. Know how to select and wear a PFD (personal flotation device). When should you wear one? What are the laws in your state regarding PFDs and children? Make sure to use appropriate sun screen or beach cover-ups to avoid getting sunburned.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(517,72,'preschool',1,'Know all beach rules for any beach you visit.  These may include things like whether or not you may have campfires or barbecues, no glass containers on the beach, colored flags to indicate wave safety (red = hazardous, stay out of the water yellow= rough, enter water with caution;  green= calm, feel free to swim).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(518,72,'level1',2,'Know basic water safety rules. Some basic water safety rules include: The best way to stay safe in the water is to learn to swim. Know what the depth markers, buoys, and flags mean in lakes or oceans. Test the water temperature before you plunge in. Cold water can shock your body and make your blood pressure and heart rate go up. You might accidentally open your mouth to yell and accidentally breathe in some water. Cold water can also slow your muscles, making it hard to swim.  Always obey all water rules. Never swim without a buddy. Never dive into shallow or murky water. Never dive into water with submerged obstacles such as rocks or trees. Never swim without an adult present. Swim at a depth that is safe for you. If you’re just learning to swim, stay near the shore. If you swim in an ocean, pond, lake, or river the fish swimming around won’t hurt you. They may hide jagged rocks, broken bottles, or trash however. Wear something to protect your feet. Also, watch out for mud, weeds, kelp, and grass, which can trap even a good swimmer. If you panic and try to yank yourself free, you may get even more tangled. Instead, shake and pull your arms an legs slowly to work yourself loose or call for an adult’s help. Don’t chew gum or eat while you swim — you could choke. Stop swimming or boating as soon as you see or hear a storm. Remember, lightning is electricity — electricity and water are a dangerous combination. If you find yourself in trouble and someone comes to rescue you in deep water, remain calm and do not grab a hold of your rescuer. If you interfere with your rescuer you can both drown. Stay calm and let them “tow” you to safety. Know how to select and wear a PFD (personal flotation device). When should you wear one? What are the laws in your state regarding PFDs and children? Make sure to use appropriate sun screen or beach cover-ups to avoid getting sunburned.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(519,72,'level1',3,'Know all beach rules for any beach you visit.  These may include things like whether or not you may have campfires or barbecues, no glass containers on the beach, colored flags to indicate wave safety (red = hazardous, stay out of the water yellow= rough, enter water with caution;  green= calm, feel free to swim).');
