INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1209,164,'preschool',0,'Learn what communicating means. “Communicating” is how we talk to each other in various ways. Make a list of the ways in which we can communicate with each other (telephone, email, instant messaging, or chat room, letter, texting, telegraph, fax machine, CB radio, etc). For communication to be effective both people must understand what they are saying to each other.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1210,164,'preschool',1,'How can we communicate safely? Talk with an adult about how to use the different ways of communication safely and who it is safe to talk to.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1211,164,'level1',2,'Learn to use one of the forms of communication you have on your list from Preschool requirement 1.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1212,164,'level2',3,'but learn about two different forms of communication.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1213,164,'level2',4,'Choose a form of communication, such as the telephone or telegraph, and find out who invented it, and when.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1214,164,'level3',5,'but learn about three forms of communication and their inventors.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1215,164,'level3',6,'Make a timeline of when different communication forms were invented and by whom, and show it to your family or troop. You must have at least 10 items on your timeline.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1216,164,'level4',7,'but learn about at least four forms of communications, and have 15 items on your timeline.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1217,164,'level4',8,'Choose a form of communication and learn the mechanics of how it works.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1218,164,'level5',9,'Do Level requirements 1 & 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1219,164,'level5',10,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1220,165,'preschool',0,'Brainstorm a list of safety rules and laws in your community that help to keep you safe such as the use of crosswalks, street lights, bike helmets, etc. Discuss why it is important to obey safety rules.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1221,165,'preschool',1,'Learn about stranger safety. What should you do if a stranger ever tries to talk to you or even take you somewhere?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1222,165,'level1',2,'Go out into your community and find evidence of community safety. Where are there things like crosswalks and street lights? Why do you think they are located where they are? Do you see people observing the safety rules? If not, why do you think they are not?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1223,165,'level2',3,'Choose a community safety issue and create a poster to teach people how to be safe. You could create a poster of safety rules for hikers, bicyclist, safe ways to get on and off the bus, cross the street, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1224,165,'level3',4,'Learn about internet safety. Understand the risks of chat rooms and meeting people online. Understand proper search techniques to avoid getting sites you don’t want. Understand safety concerns regarding making purchases online. Understand that what gets uploaded onto the internet is permanent and will make its way to places you may not want so never post personal information and make sure any photos you upload are photos you don’t mind showing to the world.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1225,165,'level4',5,'Find out what public services there are that help protect your community. What public service would you notify if you found a lost child, oil in a local creek, or have been bitten by a dog?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1226,165,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1231,168,'preschool',0,'Learn the names of at least two card games people play to compete (such as Uno, or Pokémon) and look at the type of cards used to play.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1232,168,'preschool',1,'Learn to play a simple card game with family or friends where someone wins and someone loses such as War. Practice taking turns and being a good sport.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1233,168,'level1',2,'Learn the basic rules for one competitive card game and play it at least three times.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1234,168,'level2',3,'Learn how to win and lose respectfully in a competitive game. Talk about what it means to have good sportsmanship.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1235,168,'level3',4,'Choose a competitive card game that uses strategy (such as Uno, Pokémon, Magic: The Gathering, Yu-Gi-Oh!). Learn the different strategies players use to win.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1236,168,'level4',5,'Learn how card tournaments are run. Explore rules, rankings, and how fairness is maintained in competitions.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1237,168,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead. Optional Requirements');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1238,169,'preschool',0,'.  Learn what a composer is. Be able to name at least one composer. Listen to at least one piece of their music. Did you like it? Why or why not?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1239,169,'level1',1,'.  Do Preschool requirement 1 *. Be able to name at least 3 composers, and listen to at least 2 pieces each of their work.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1240,169,'level1',2,'.  What is the difference between a composer and a songwriter?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1241,169,'level2',3,'.  Do Level 1 requirements 1 & 2. Be able to name at least 5 composers, and listen to at least three pieces each of their work.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1242,169,'level2',4,'.  Be able to identify 3 composers from pictures or portraits. (If you earned this badge at a different level, learn to identify three other composers.)');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1243,169,'level3',5,'.  Do Level 2 requirements 1 & 2. Be able to name at least 10 composers.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1244,169,'level3',6,'.  Many composers played instruments as well as composing. Find at least five composers who also played at least one instrument. Who played the most instruments?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1245,169,'level4',7,'.  Do Level 3 requirements 1 & 2.  Be able to name at least 15 composers.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1246,169,'level4',8,'.  Read a biography of a composer.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1247,169,'level5',9,'.  Do Level 4 requirements 1 & 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1248,169,'level5',10,'.  Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1249,170,'preschool',0,'What is compost? What is it good for? What types of food can and cannot go into home compost? Why? Understand basic safety rules for working around a compost pile and know why it is important to wash well when you are done.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1250,170,'preschool',1,'Watch some food decompose – like letting a pumpkin rot. Discuss how it changes with an adult.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1251,170,'level1',2,'Do compost in a bottle project or set up a compost pile in your yard.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1252,170,'level1',3,'What are decomposers? And how do they help in the composting process. What does heat do for the decomposition process? Will things decompose even without heat?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1253,170,'level2',4,'While watching food decompose in a compost heap, document it by drawing or photographing it at various stages.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1254,170,'level2',5,'Understand Primary Consumers, Secondary Consumers, Tertiary Consumers and the role each plays in composting.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1255,170,'level3',6,'What do you need to mix together to have an effective compost pile? Understand why an effective mix is essential to a good compost pile.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1256,170,'level4',7,'Why is air/aeration so important for making compost? Can food compost if there is no or low oxygen? Be aware that anaerobic composting is usually slow and smelly.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1257,170,'level4',8,'What are the four stages of Compost? Understand each one and what is happening both chemically and physically during each stage. The four phases include: The mesophilic phase The thermophilic phase The cooling phase The curing phase');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1258,170,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1259,171,'preschool',0,'What is a computer? How does it differ from other common electronic devices?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1260,171,'preschool',1,'Learn about proper computer safety and discuss these rules with a parent or guardian. Why is it important to handle and use a computer correctly?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1261,171,'level1',2,'Learn how to use the basic features of your computer. How do you turn it on/off? How do you navigate? What basic programs are there?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1262,171,'level2',3,'Learn the basic programs of your computer. For instance, how do you access the internet? What about any computer games? A word processor or other software?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1263,171,'level2',4,'Learn the history of the computer. Who invented it? How has it progressed over the years? How has computer technology been used in things like phones, cars, and television? Make a timeline of at least ten major events and changes the computer has undergone.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1264,171,'level3',5,'Find a computer program that allows you to do something you haven’t tried before and learn it. Examples might be an interior design program that allows you to design your dream bedroom, a personal finance software package, photo or video editing program, a digital scrap booking program, or a foreign language program.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1265,171,'level3',6,'Using your preferred word processor, learn how to: Change font size Change fonts Change font color Highlight text Change the line spacing Change the margins Create a title Create a header Create a table of contents Insert an image, resize it, and reposition it Insert a page number Insert a footnote');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1266,171,'level4',7,'Find out what you should look for when buying a computer. What are the main three brands of computers? Would you buy a pre-built computer or build your own? What do each of the parts do? How much memory do you need if you are just using a computer for school? What about gaming? What is RAM and how much do you need?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1267,171,'level5',8,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead. Optional Requirements');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1270,173,'preschool',0,'Learn at least three different ways you can save water at home. Examples might include turning off the faucet when you brush your teeth or only filling the bathtub to 6 inches or less.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1271,173,'level1',1,'Make a list or draw how you and your family could reduce the amount of electricity used at home. For two weeks, track the ways you saved water and electricity at home. Discuss what you are doing with your family and have them conserve water and electricity as well. At the end of two weeks, discuss with your parents how successful your family was in reducing the amount of water and electricity they used.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1272,173,'level2',2,'Learn about what you and your family can do to reduce the amount of heat needed to keep your house warm in the winter. For two weeks, track the ways you saved heat at home as well as water and electricity.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1273,173,'level3',3,'Bring your own non-disposable cup, eating utensils, and plate to use at camp or bring a garbage-free lunch to school or work for at least one week.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1274,173,'level4',4,'With the help of an adult, check the tire pressure in a car to see if the tires are properly inflated. Learn how proper air pressure can reduce gas consumption as well as save wear and tear on the tires.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1275,173,'level5',5,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1276,174,'preschool',0,'Learn basic kitchen safety while baking.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1277,174,'preschool',1,'Taste three different kinds of cookies.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1278,174,'level1',2,'Taste four different kinds of cookies.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1279,174,'level1',3,'Find examples of at least one cookie in the following different categories: Bar Drop Sandwich Cut-out Spritz No Bake Your example can be a real cookie or a picture of one. How do they differ in look and ingredients?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1280,174,'level2',4,'Taste five different kinds of cookies.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1281,174,'level2',5,'Learn the history of cookies throughout the ages. Pick ten and learn the following information about them: When was this particular cookie invented? Who invented it? Did it have a different name other than what it is now known as? Learn one interesting fact');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1282,174,'level3',6,'Taste six different kinds of cookies.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1283,174,'level3',7,'Learn about cookies from different countries, such as a Finnish pinwheels or Italian pizzelle. Pick five different countries and research one cookie from each. Where do fortune cookies come from?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1284,174,'level4',8,'Taste seven different kinds of cookies.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1285,174,'level4',9,'Bake three different types of cookies from scratch. (Cookies made for optional requirements must be in addition to these cookies).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1286,174,'level5',10,'Taste nine different kinds of cookies.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1287,174,'level5',11,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1288,175,'preschool',0,'Learn and understand basic kitchen safety including: Adult supervision is mandatory. Ovens, knives and bubbling pots can become potential accidents when kids are left on their own in the kitchen. Instill cleanliness by washing hands in hot soapy water before and after handling food, pulling back long hair, or cleaning counter-tops. Always return unused portions of perishable foods, like dairy products and meats, to the refrigerator right after using them. Don’t let them sit out on the counter. Show how to select a microwaveable bowl and to use pot holders when removing containers from the oven. When shaping foods with hands, do not lick your fingers or put your hands in your mouth. This is especially important with raw foods, such as cookie dough and meat. Direct sneezes and coughs away from food, use a tissue to cover mouth and nose, and wash hands immediately afterward. Instead of wiping hands on dish towels after handling raw meats, use paper towels. If a dish towel comes in contact with raw meats or their juices, immediately remove it from the kitchen for laundering. Check that the oven and other cooking appliances are turned off before you leave the kitchen. Keep electrical appliances away from water to avoid shocks. Stay away from electrical sockets, especially if your hands are wet. If you burn yourself, tell an adult immediately and hold the burned area under cool running water. Don’t put knives or other sharp objects into a sink full of water. Someone could reach in and get hurt. Watch out for sharp knives. Let an adult cut or slice foods or help you do it. Don’t put cooked food on an unwashed plate or cutting board that held raw food. Always use a clean plate. Always turn pot handles in toward the back of the range top. This way no one can bump into them and knock the pot over. Keep paper towels, dish towels and pot holders away from the range top so they don’t catch on fire.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1289,175,'preschool',1,'Cook one recipe with the help of an adult that requires measuring at least three items.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1290,175,'level1',2,'Learn what the following kitchen tools are and what they are used for: Pot Pan Flat Spatula Rubber Spatula Mixer Measuring Cups Measuring Spoons Pie Dish Cookie Sheet Cutting Board');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1291,175,'level2',3,'and add the following safety rules and kitchen tool knowledge: Never put water on a cooking fire — it could make the fire bigger. Ask an adult for help! Put out a fire with a fire extinguisher. If the fire is small, it can be put out with baking soda or smothered with a lid. Leave the house and call 911 if the fire has leaping flames. Never add water to a pan that has hot oil in it. It could make the oil splatter and burn someone. Level 2 members may use sharp knives to cut items such as fruits and vegetables, but must have adult supervision. Make sure you always cut away from your body.  Keep in mind that sharp knives are safer than dull ones as they cut cleanly and do not slip as easily. Demonstrate how to use stove top burners, preheat an oven, and transfer things in and out of an over safely. Know what the following kitchen tools are and what they are used for: Whisk Ladle Baster Brush Slotted Spoons Tongs Grater Double Boiler Bundt Pan Spring Form Pan Broiling Pan Garlic Press Masher Pastry Cutter Paring Knife Butcher Knife Bread Knife');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1292,175,'level2',4,'Learn what it means to bake, broil, boil, fry, grill, and roast, and demonstrate how to measure dry, liquid and solid ingredients.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1293,175,'level3',5,'Know what each of the following cooking terms means: Al dente Baste Blanch Braise Clarify Curdle Egg Wash Julienne Marinate Parboil Puree Roux Sauté Sear Sift Simmer Skim Steep Truss Unleavened Whip Whisk Zest');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1294,175,'level4',6,'Learn at least three different cuts of each type of meat and how they are best cooked. Then cook one you have never tried before. Beef: blade roast, pot roast, rib roast, skirt steak, flank steak, rib eye, top sirloin, ribs, ground, etc. Veal: breast, shoulder blade roast, rib chops, rib crown roast, leg sirloin steak, cubed steak, cutlets, etc. Pork: loin chops, butterfly chops, sausage, bacon, shoulder arm roast, cubed steaks, ham, hocks, country style ribs, loin back ribs, etc. Lamb: shoulder blade chops, breast, breast riblets, shank, rib crown roast, leg, ground, etc. Fish: fillet, steak, chunk, whole, etc. Poultry: giblets, neck, leg, thigh, wing, breast, back, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1295,175,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1296,176,'preschool',0,'Watch two people give cooking demonstrations. These can be in person, on T.V. or online (with a parent’s permission). Which one did you like better? Why? What did you learn by watching the demonstrations?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1297,176,'level1',1,'Do Penguin requirement 1.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1298,176,'level1',2,'Show someone how to do something related to cooking that involves at least three steps. You may do this demonstration with another person.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1299,176,'level2',3,'Watch three people giving demonstrations, either in person, on T.V. or online (with a parent’s permission).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1300,176,'level2',4,'Perform a cooking demonstration that involves at least four steps. There must be several items you prepare ahead of time. You may do this demonstration with another person.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1301,176,'level3',5,'Watch four people give cooking demonstrations, either in person, on T.V. or online (with a parent’s permission).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1302,176,'level3',6,'Perform two cooking demonstrations that involve at least five steps or two demonstrations with three steps each. There must be several items you prepare ahead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1303,176,'level4',7,'Watch five people give cooking demonstrations, either in person, on T.V. or online (with a parent’s permission).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1304,176,'level4',8,'Perform three cooking demos that involve at least five steps OR a demo in front of a large group. Plan out your demo ahead of time, making sure that you have all equipment, ingredients, script, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1305,176,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1307,178,'preschool',0,'What is a coral reef? Understand that corals are animals, and a reef is made up of living and dead corals and serves as a home to many tropical fish.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1308,178,'preschool',1,'Look at pictures or videos of five different types of reef-building coral. Learn their names.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1309,178,'level1',2,'Learn the three different types of coral reefs and how to recognize them.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1310,178,'level2',3,'Know the rules of safe and responsible swimming, snorkeling and diving when around coral reefs, such as not touching reefs and not anchoring your boat on reefs. Understand the importance of using reef-friendly sunscreen or rash guards during beach days instead of using sunscreens that can kill corals.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1311,178,'level3',4,'Identify at least five major threats to coral reefs (e.g., climate change, pollution, overfishing). Explain how each threat impacts coral reefs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1312,178,'level4',5,'Learn the life cycle of coral.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1313,178,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1314,179,'preschool',0,'Learn safety rule when people are using the following:  Scissors and cutting blades, glue, hot glue, pins and needles, and hot air guns.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1315,179,'preschool',1,'Make a costume accessory such as a crown, necklace or cape.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1316,179,'level1',2,'Many costumes can be made of everyday items.  Brainstorm how you could use the following items in a costume: cardboard box, zip ties, egg carton, a sheet, paper bag,  and balloons.  Now choose at least one everyday item and create a costume piece out of it.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1317,179,'level2',3,'Modify an existing garment to turn it into a costume.  For example, you could dye a wedding dress to turn it into a princess gown.  Or you could cut the sleeves off a jacket to create a vest.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1318,179,'level3',4,'Learn how to hand stitch the following:  Running Stich, Catch Stitch, Herringbone Stitch, Blind Hem Stitch');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1319,179,'level4',5,'Learn how to properly take a person’s measurements including neck, bust, waist, hips, front waist length, back waist length, shoulder, arm length, and inseam.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1320,179,'level5',6,'Do Levle 4 requirements 1 & 2');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1321,179,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your newfound knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead. Optional Requirements');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1322,180,'preschool',0,'Learn about three ethnic costumes. Where are they from? Find the countries on a map.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1323,180,'preschool',1,'Learn about historical costumes from where you live such as Native Americans, the Colonial Period, the Pioneer Period, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1324,180,'level1',2,'Know what the costumes were made from and what they were used for.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1325,180,'level1',3,'Draw or create (out of a material of your choice) a costume from a country of your choice.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1326,180,'level2',4,'Pick a country and learn about their historical costumes. Are there pictures you can find of them? Was there a protective reason that they wore what they did? Symbolic reasons? Learn what a nobleman might have worn in comparison to a peasant.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1327,180,'level3',5,'Find out what different countries used, and still use, for costumes in social events, weddings, birthdays, funerals, baptisms, coming of age or events special to that specific country such as a quinceanera.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1328,180,'level4',6,'Pick two countries and learn about their costumes. Learn accessories that went along with them. Did they wear hats, shoes, carry purses, or have other accessories? Compare their historical costumes to what they wear in everyday life now. Is it the same or different? Learn about their fancier clothing. What was considered “fancy”? What constituted as a event worthy of wearing that kind of clothing?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1329,180,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1330,181,'preschool',0,'When would you wear a costume? Come up with three ideas of places you would wear a costume and think of an appropriate costume to wear.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1331,181,'level1',1,'Discuss how the character of an actor should influence what he or she wears. Should an evil character wear the same thing as someone good and kind? Should a fifteen-year-old girl wear the exact same outfit as her grandmother? How can you make an actor look rich or poor?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1332,181,'level2',2,'Find out what historical periods are and how clothing has changed with various eras. How have clothes changed depending on which country you live? Be able to describe a North American, South American, African, Asian, and European costume unique to a country in each of those continents. You can look at a picture while you describe it.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1333,181,'level3',3,'For the five costumes from five continents, learn the ethnic names of any pieces you’ve chosen.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1334,181,'level3',4,'Put together a costume for yourself or someone else for a party, skit, or other occasion, making sure you stay “in character” for the entire outfit.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1335,181,'level4',5,'Design a minimum of three complete outfits for a whole family or group for a play or celebration (think Goldilocks and the Three Bears or a Pilgrim family).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1336,181,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead. Optional Requirements');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1337,182,'preschool',0,'Learn what a state or county fair is.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1338,182,'preschool',1,'Visit a state or country fair.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1339,182,'level1',2,'Learn what type of items and animals are shown at your fair.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1340,182,'level2',3,'Learn the history of county and state fairs.  Why did they originally start?  How have they spread and grown?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1341,182,'level3',4,'Learn the history of the fair of your choice. Create a timeline of events with at least 10 items.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1342,182,'level4',5,'Learn about a famous fair such as one of the World’s Fairs. Are any of them still open to the public?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1343,182,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1344,183,'preschool',0,'Talk to an adult about what courage means and how you can show it in your own life.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1345,183,'level1',1,'How does the dictionary define courage?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1346,183,'level1',2,'What is the difference between courage and recklessness?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1347,183,'level2',3,'Demonstrate courage in your own life by doing something difficult for you that takes courage. Examples might be riding a roller coaster for the first time, going skiing, trying a new food you are not sure you will like, getting a shot at the doctor’s office, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1348,183,'level3',4,'Read a biography or watch a movie about someone who exhibited courage. What can you learn from their life?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1349,183,'level4',5,'Make a list of your fears (at least 5) and then make a step by step plan as to how you can overcome each one.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1350,183,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1351,184,'preschool',0,'What is a cowboy or cowgirl? What do they do?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1352,184,'preschool',1,'Find three pictures of a cowboy/girl doing different jobs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1353,184,'level1',2,'Find out what kind of jobs a cowboy or cowgirl does. How do the jobs they do today differ from what they did back in the 1800’s?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1354,184,'level2',3,'Visit the National Cowboy or Cowgirl Museum and Hall of Fame either in person or online (with a parent’s permission). Read about at least three of the men or women in their hall of fame. If you do not have internet access, check out books on cowgirls from the library to look through.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1355,184,'level3',4,'and read about two cowboys or cowgirls and five men or women in the Cowgirl Hall of Fame.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1356,184,'level3',5,'Find out about the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) or the Women’s Pro Rodeo Association (WPRA). Also learn about the Working Ranch Cowboys Association (WRCA) or the Women’s Ranch Rodeo Association (WRRA). What are their sanctioned events? Know what each event entails.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1357,184,'level4',6,'and read about three cowboys or cowgirls.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1358,184,'level4',7,'Find out about careers for modern day cowboys/girls. What type of education do you need? What hours and pay can you expect? Interview someone with a job in this field.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1359,184,'level5',8,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1360,185,'preschool',0,'Learn about the different materials you can use for crafts. List as many as you can think of, such as paper, glue, paint, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1361,185,'preschool',1,'Make a card for someone you care about. It can be a birthday card, get well card, greeting card, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1362,185,'level1',2,'Learn about basic wood working. Make a simple project such as a box or bird house. You can complete this requirement with an adult’s help.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1363,185,'level2',3,'Learn to decoupage something. Decoupage is the art of decorating an object by gluing colored paper cutouts onto it and then sealing with decoupage glue. Decorate a picture frame, Christmas ornament, box, or other item using decoupage. Find out the difference between matte and glossy decoupage as well as the difference between decoupage meant for indoor or outdoor use.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1364,185,'level3',4,'Learn to scrap book. Find examples of scrap book pages you like either in magazines or online. Using patterned paper, stickers, fancy scissors, and other embellishments, create at least three different scrapbook pages.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1365,185,'level4',5,'Learn beading and create at least three pieces of jewelry for yourself using at least three different types of beads and techniques.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1366,185,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1367,186,'preschool',0,'Know what a crepe is and how it differs from a pancake.  How are they similar?  How are they different?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1368,186,'preschool',1,'Taste at least one savory crepe and one sweet crepe.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1369,186,'level1',2,'Complete Preschool requirements 1 & 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1370,186,'level1',3,'Help to make a batch of crepes.  Make sure to learn and follow all kitchen safety rules.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1371,186,'level2',4,'Complete Level 1 requirements 1 & 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1372,186,'level2',5,'What is the history of crepes? What country are they from? Who created it?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1373,186,'level3',6,'Complete Level 2 requirements 1 & 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1374,186,'level3',7,'What is a crepe pan? How is it different from using a sauté pan?  Why does it work better for making crepes?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1375,186,'level4',8,'Complete Level 3y requirements 1 & 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1376,186,'level4',9,'Can you make a crepe batter in advance? Does it have to be used right away? What are some of the safety aspects you have to think about when making crepes?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1377,186,'level5',10,'Do Levl 4 requirements 1 & 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1378,186,'level5',11,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone.  You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge.   If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1379,187,'preschool',0,'What are fingerprints? Discuss with an adult how no two people have the same fingerprints. Look at your hands and examine the patterns of your fingers.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1380,187,'preschool',1,'Understand the basic definition of forensics and why it is useful.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1381,187,'level1',2,'Using an ink pad and card stock (or cards from local law enforcement), take fingerprints. Learn about loops, whorls, and arches. Identify examples of each in the fingerprints you took.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1382,187,'level2',3,'Learn to dust for fingerprints. Which surfaces/materials work best for taking fingerprints? What are some additional ways to check for fingerprints? Explain the process of evaluating a crime scene and discuss how you would search for and gather fingerprints.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1383,187,'level3',4,'What are the different types of evidence? What are the divisions/sections of a forensics lab? What types of evidence are included in each? Discuss how different type of evidence are collected from a crime scene.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1384,187,'level4',5,'Learn about the history of crime scene investigation (forensic science). How has science and technology changed this? Create a timeline showing your findings. What role do forensic scientists play in crime scene investigation?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1385,187,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead Optional Requirements');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1386,188,'preschool',0,'Be able to recognize when something has been crocheted, such as a blanket or scarf. Know what equipment is needed to crochet: Crochet hooks Yarn Scissors A bag to keep your projects in.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1387,188,'preschool',1,'Discuss safety and cleanliness. Why should you wash your hands before crocheting? How should you handle crochet hooks? How much light do you need when you crochet? Is the re a type of crochet hook that’s safer than others? How should you handle scissors?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1388,188,'level1',2,'Understand the difference in the size of crochet hooks and how this affects your project. Look at and feel at least three different types of yarn and discuss the benefits of each.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1389,188,'level2',3,'Learn crochet terminology: Chain Single crochet Double crochet Slipknot Fasten off');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1390,188,'level2',4,'Crochet a dishcloth, a potholder, or a scarf for a doll or stuffed animal.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1391,188,'level3',5,'Learn to read crochet patterns.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1392,188,'level3',6,'If you are beginner at crocheting, make a dishcloth, potholder, or scarf. If you are not a beginner, crochet something you’ve never made before.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1393,188,'level4',7,'Learn how to increase and decrease stitches or learn to crochet in a circle.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1394,188,'level5',8,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1395,189,'preschool',0,'Find out which sort of objects are often decorated with cross stitch (such as bookmarks and towels).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1396,189,'preschool',1,'Learn what is needed for a cross stitch project, such as a needle, thread, hoop, pattern, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1397,189,'level1',2,'What is the difference between counted cross stitch and stamped?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1398,189,'level1',3,'Look through a variety of cross stitch designs and patterns.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1399,189,'level2',4,'Complete a simple cross stitch project.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1400,189,'level3',5,'Learn about each of these method and how to use them in a project: In line waste knot method Away knot method Stitching over method Stitching cross stitch Ending a thread Half stitch Quarter stitch Three quarter stitch Back stitch French knot Embellishments');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1401,189,'level4',6,'Use graph paper and design your own cross stitch pattern by placing a colored X in each box.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1402,189,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1403,190,'preschool',0,'Learn what an cruise ship is. Look at pictures of different cruise ships. Which is your favorite?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1404,190,'level1',1,'List 3 different cruise lines and how to tell the ships apart.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1405,190,'level2',2,'Learn to identify at least four different cruise lines.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1406,190,'level2',3,'Make a timeline of cruise ship history with at least 10 items and learn about one famous event in cruise line history in depth.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1407,190,'level3',4,'Have at least 10 items on your timeline.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1408,190,'level3',5,'Research a cruise you’d like to take. How many days is the trip? Where does it go? Why does it interest you? What does it cost?  What are your lodging options?  What is included?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1409,190,'level4',6,'Have at least 15 items on your timeline.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1410,190,'level4',7,'Learn the science behind how a cruise ship floats.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1411,190,'level5',8,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1412,191,'preschool',0,'Learn what a cryptid is. Are they real or imaginary, or something in between?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1413,191,'preschool',1,'Read a story about a cryptid.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1414,191,'level1',2,'Learn about three famous cryptids such as: the Yeti, Sasquatch, Bigfoot, the Abominable Snowman, or the Loch Ness Monster.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1415,191,'level2',3,'Learn about animals once considered cryptids that are now known to exist, like the platypus, giant squid, and komodo dragon. Why didn’t people think they existed?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1416,191,'level3',4,'Learn about an extinct species that has been resurrected to cryptid status.  Why do people think these animals still exist?  A good example is the ivory-billed woodpecker featured in the documentary Ghost Bird.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1417,191,'level4',5,'Investigate the history of cryptids around the world including folklore and myths associated with cryptids in various cultures.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1418,191,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1419,192,'preschool',0,'Choose a culture you would like to learn about.  Listen to a song, story, or traditional music from this culture.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1420,192,'preschool',1,'Sample foods from the country. Learn what its citizens eat for meals and snacks. Is it similar or different from what you might eat?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1421,192,'level1',2,'Find your chosen country on a map. What continent is it on? What is the capital city? What countries border it?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1422,192,'level2',3,'Learn what language is spoken in your chosen country. Be able to introduce yourself in that language, and say please and thank you as well as count to 10.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1423,192,'level3',4,'Research a famous historical or modern figure from the culture and describe what they are known for.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1424,192,'level4',5,'Look at the money from your selected country. What is it called? Who are the people and what are the symbols on it? Find out the exchange rate and see how much it would take to buy something in that country. Price out ten different items and compare them to how much they would cost in your chosen country.  How does the cost of goods and services affect this culture.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1425,192,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1426,193,'preschool',0,'Understand what a dairy is. Look at pictures of a dairy, visit a dairy or view one on video or online. What kinds of animals are usually milked in a dairy?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1427,193,'level1',1,'Be able to recognize and describe three different breeds of dairy cow or dairy goat.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1428,193,'level1',2,'Know the difference, in females, between a calf, a heifer, and a cow or a kid and a doe.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1429,193,'level2',3,'What equipment do you need to properly care for and milk a cow or goat? What type of shelter do they need, feed, veterinarian care, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1430,193,'level3',4,'Be able to describe three diseases of cows, the prevention, and the cure, if any.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1431,193,'level4',5,'Know how to milk a cow or goat by hand or to strip after machine milking and know the care of the udders before milking.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1432,193,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1433,194,'preschool',0,'Make something using a decoupage technique.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1434,194,'preschool',1,'Learn the difference between matte and glossy glue,');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1435,194,'level1',2,'Learn about different types of brushes. Which work best for decoupage and why? Learn how to properly clean your brushes after decoupage so that they are not ruined by the glue.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1436,194,'level2',3,'Learn about the history of decoupage.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1437,194,'level3',4,'Learn about the durability of decoupage. What types of glue are available for indoor or outdoor use? Which glues will dissolve when they get wet? What inks will run when a decoupage technique is applied? Is there something you can apply over the decoupage to increase the durability? Practice using different papers for decoupage, examples might include: Magazine clippings Tissue paper Paper napkins Labels Gift wrap Photographs Greeting cards Computer print outs Old picture books');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1438,194,'level4',5,'Complete a decoupage project on three of the following surfaces: Wood Metal Glass Plastic Cardboard or Paper Mache Stone Craft Foam');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1439,194,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1440,195,'preschool',0,'Learn how to properly brush your teeth and the amount of toothpaste to use. Learn how to properly floss your teeth.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1441,195,'preschool',1,'Learn toothbrush safety rules, such as never run with a toothbrush, don’t share toothbrushes, toothbrushes are not toys, replace your toothbrush after being sick, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1442,195,'level1',2,'Learn what cavities are and how you get them. How can you prevent cavities? Learn the difference between “baby teeth” and “permanent teeth.”');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1443,195,'level2',3,'Learn the difference between plaque and cavities. What are some of the ways that you can prevent plaque from turning into cavities?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1444,195,'level3',4,'Learn about dental care while wearing braces. What are the do’s and don’ts of flossing, brushing and foods to avoid?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1445,195,'level4',5,'Learn about gingivitis, periodontitis, and one other dental disease. What are the causes and how can they be prevented?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1446,195,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1447,196,'preschool',0,'What is digital movie making? Be able to explain the simple definition to someone.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1448,196,'preschool',1,'What items do you need to make a digital movie? Discuss with your family, friends, or group different equipment and props you might need. Help to make a digital movie both by performing in one and in helping to film one.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1449,196,'level1',2,'Learn how to run your camera and how to keep it still while you film. Discuss with your family, friends, or group why this is a very important technique and what kinds of equipment you might need to accomplish this. Practice filming for at least 15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1450,196,'level2',3,'Learn what type of video software is available for making digital movies.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1451,196,'level2',4,'Learn about shot selections (wide shot, establishing shot, cutaway shot, close up, tracking shot, etc.) and the differences between them. Write a description of each and give examples of how each is shown on the film. Practice filming for at least 20 minutes, using some of these techniques.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1452,196,'level3',5,'Learn how to properly cut the film between dialog and how to change camera angles between scenes. Write a short report focusing on proper cutting techniques and practice filming for at least 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1453,196,'level4',6,'Learn about movie editing software (Windows Movie Maker, iMovie, and Avidemux are three examples). Compare prices and usability of the different software. Choose one software that you can have access to and learn how to edit the filming you did in previous requirements.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1454,196,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead. Optional Requirements');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1459,199,'preschool',0,'Learn to identify at least three different dinosaurs. What does the word dinosaur mean?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1460,199,'preschool',1,'What are the differences between carnivores and herbivores? Be able to name at least one dinosaur from each category.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1461,199,'level1',2,'Learn to identify five different dinosaurs');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1462,199,'level1',3,'Find out why the scientists think the dinosaurs became extinct.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1463,199,'level2',4,'Identify seven different dinosaurs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1464,199,'level2',5,'Dinosaurs were in existence during the Mesozoic Era, called “The Age of Reptiles.” Choose a time period such as the Triassic,  the Jurassic, or the Cretaceous, and choose one dinosaur to learn more about in that period.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1465,199,'level3',6,'Identify nine different dinosaurs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1466,199,'level3',7,'Dinosaurs are usually named after a trait, the area they were found or the person who discovered them. The name is converted into Greek or Latin. Choose three dinosaurs and find out the meaning of their names. If you found a new species of dinosaur, what would you name it?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1467,199,'level4',8,'Identify eleven different dinosaurs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1468,199,'level4',9,'Paleontologists use lots of different tools to prepare fossils. Learn about three different tools and how they are used in fossil preparation. Fossils are very delicate and expensive. Most museums have casts of dinosaur bones on display rather than the real thing. Learn how fossils are preserved.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1469,199,'level5',10,'Identify thirteen different dinosaurs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1470,199,'level5',11,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1473,201,'preschool',0,'Choose a disease or genetic disorder to study. Learn the basic symptoms and complications of this disease and who it usually affects. What part of the body is affected?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1474,201,'preschool',1,'Is there a specific color or symbol associated with this disease or genetic disorder to help bring awareness, such as a grey ribbon for diabetes or a puzzle piece for autism? Make something to wear or display to help bring awareness to your disease.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1475,201,'level1',2,'Do an experiment or create a project that shows how your body works and what goes wrong when affected by this disease or disorder. For example, with Crohn’s disease it affects the digestive system so you could take clay and push it through a pair of nylons to simulate food moving through the intestines.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1476,201,'level2',3,'Find out how this disease or disorder is usually treated. How effective is the treatment in most cases?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1477,201,'level3',4,'Find out what associations support people with this disease/disorder or conduct research to try to find a cure. Make a list of as many groups as you can.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1478,201,'level4',5,'Participate in a community service project to support this disease/disorder. You might raise money for research, participate in a walk-a-thon, make posters, hand out ribbons, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1479,201,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1480,202,'preschool',0,'Be able to list at least five different Disney movies. Watch at least two of them.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1481,202,'preschool',1,'Be able to list at least ten different Disney characters. Which one is your favorite and why?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1482,202,'level1',2,'Be able to list ten Disney movies and twenty characters. Watch at least four Disney movies.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1483,202,'level1',3,'Learn about Walt Disney. Find out how, why, and when he started Disney.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1484,202,'level2',4,'Watch at least five Disney movies.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1485,202,'level2',5,'Create a Disney timeline with at least 25 important milestones of the company.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1486,202,'level3',6,'Find out how animated Disney movies are made. What are the latest modern techniques for animation? How has the animation changed over the years? Research the difference between 2D animation and CGI.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1487,202,'level4',7,'Disney has expanded into television, radio, movies, theme parks, toys, stage shows, cruise ships, and more. Make a list of as many Disney products in each category as you can. Can you think of any other places into which Disney could expand?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1488,202,'level5',8,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1491,205,'preschool',0,'Visit California Adventure. What are the eight different lands? Which one is your favorite?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1492,205,'preschool',1,'Explore each of the lands you listed above.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1493,205,'level1',2,'Ride at least five different rides. Which one is your favorite?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1494,205,'level2',3,'Ride at least six different rides. Pick your favorite and research its history. What year was it built? Who designed it? How does it reflect the movie its based on, if any?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1495,205,'level2',4,'Try at least five different themed snacks or treats, such as the Mickey pretzel, churro, Mickey shaped ice cream, etc. Pick your favorite and try to recreate the recipe at home.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1496,205,'level3',5,'Ride at least seven different rides. Research the history of two rides.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1497,205,'level3',6,'Research the history of Disney California Adventure. Make a timeline with at least thirty major events. When did the park first open? What were the main attractions? Which rides have been removed or added to the park over the years? Which meet-and-greet characters have come and gone? Have any of the restaurants changed?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1498,205,'level4',7,'Ride at least eight different rides. Research the history of three rides.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1499,205,'level4',8,'Make a scrapbook of your visit to the parks. You can include photos, ride ticket stubs, characters autographs, etc. It should be at least ten pages. Also include a page where you write about your experience, or include commentary on each page.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1500,205,'level5',9,'Ride at least ten different rides. Research the history of four.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1501,205,'level5',10,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1502,209,'preschool',0,'Visit Disneyland. What are the nine different themed lands? Which one is your favorite?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1503,209,'preschool',1,'Meet the “Fab Five”: Mickey Mouse, Minnie Mouse, Pluto, Goofy and Donald. If possible, take a picture or receive the autograph of each one.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1504,209,'level1',2,'Ride at least five different rides. Which one was your favorite?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1505,209,'level2',3,'Ride at least six different rides. Pick your favorite and research its history. What year was it built? Who designed it? How does it reflect the movie it’s based on, if any?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1506,209,'level2',4,'Try at least five different Disney themed foods or treats. There are many popular favorites, such as the Dole Whip, corn-dog, churro, etc.  Pick your favorite and try to recreate the recipe at home.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1507,209,'level3',5,'Ride at least seven rides. Research the history of two of them.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1508,209,'level3',6,'Research the history of Disneyland Park. Make a timeline with at least thirty major events. When did the park first open? What were the main attractions? Which rides have been removed or added to the park over the years? Which meet-and-greet characters have come and gone? Have any of the restaurants changed?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1509,209,'level4',7,'Ride at least eight rides. Research the history of three rides.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1510,209,'level4',8,'Make a scrapbook of your visit to the parks. You can include photos, ride ticket stubs, characters autographs, etc. It should be at least ten pages. Also include a page where you write about your experience, or include commentary on each page.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1511,209,'level5',9,'Ride at least ten rides. Research the history of four rides.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1512,209,'level5',10,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1513,210,'preschool',0,'Be able to identify at least 3 Disney Princesses.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1514,210,'preschool',1,'Pick a Disney princess. Does your princess have any magical or special abilities? If so, what are they? How do they use their abilities? If they don’t have their own magic, what type of magic was used for their benefit and by whom?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1515,210,'level1',2,'Be able to name and identify 5 Disney princesses and what movies they are from.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1516,210,'level1',3,'Name three good qualities that the princess of your choice has such as honesty, courage, or gentleness. Write down about how these qualities help this princess in her story.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1517,210,'level2',4,'Be able to name 7 Disney princesses, the movies they are from, and the kingdoms they live in.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1518,210,'level2',5,'Learn one song from the Disney princess movie you have chosen.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1519,210,'level3',6,'Be able to name 10 Disney princesses, their kingdom, the movie they are from and at least one other character in the movie that helps the princess.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1520,210,'level3',7,'Learn who was the main artist(s) and who was the voice of your favorite Disney princess as well as the year your Disney princess movie was made. Find out if your specific Disney princess’s look or voice was based off of a real person.  If so, who?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1521,210,'level4',8,'Be able to name every Disney princess, their kingdom, the movie they are from and 3 other characters and how they influence the princess for good or bad.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1522,210,'level4',9,'Find out what time era and area of the world your Disney Princess was based on.  How would the story change if it were set in modern times and locations?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1523,210,'level5',10,'Create a timeline of the Disney Princess movies.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1524,210,'level5',11,'Teach someone else a skill learned in this badge.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1525,212,'preschool',0,'Know what Doctor Who is. Be able to recognize the T.A.R.D.I.S. Discuss time travel with someone who watches the show.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1526,212,'preschool',1,'Talk about some TV shows you watch, or books you read, that have talking animals, plants or trees. Compare how the shows or books differ from the world you live in.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1527,212,'level1',2,'With a parent’s permission and supervision, watch three episodes of Doctor Who.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1528,212,'level2',3,'but watch five episodes of Doctor Who. Learn the following things about the T.A.R.D.I.S.: What does “T.A.R.D.I.S” stand for? How can people who travel in the T.A.R.D.I.S. understand languages they do not know? What is a chameleon circuit? What kind of systems does the T.A.R.D.I.S. have? How many rooms are inside? What kind of objects has the T.A.R.D.I.S. turned into?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1529,212,'level2',4,'Create a timeline of the history of Doctor Who. Include a minimum of 10 items.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1530,212,'level3',5,'but watch seven episodes of Doctor Who with at least three different Doctors and include at least 15 items on your timeline.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1531,212,'level3',6,'Find out what a Time Lord is. What does it mean to “regenerate”? Learn about the life cycle of a Time Lord (regeneration), and how many regenerations a time lord may have. How do you tell the difference between a time lord and other beings?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1532,212,'level4',7,'but watch at least one episode from each regeneration of the Doctor. Have at least 20 items on your timeline.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1533,212,'level4',8,'Each regeneration of the Doctor is different. Describe each Doctor’s appearance, dress, and personality. Explain how each character is designed to appeal specifically to the audience of his or her generation. Discuss why you think this TV show has had such a huge following for so many years.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1534,212,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1535,213,'preschool',0,'What are male and female dogs called? What are the babies called? What are young dogs called? What is a group of dogs called?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1536,213,'preschool',1,'Learn how to properly behave around dogs and how to hold a puppy or small dog so that neither you, nor the dog, gets hurt.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1537,213,'level1',2,'Be able to identify three different breeds of dogs. Be able to identify at least five different points of their anatomy.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1538,213,'level2',3,'Identify at least five different breeds of dog.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1539,213,'level2',4,'Learn about the life cycle of dog. How long do they live? How many babies do they normally have? Why do smaller dogs tend to live longer than bigger ones?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1540,213,'level3',5,'Identify at least ten different breeds of dog.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1541,213,'level3',6,'Describe at least three different dog diseases, their symptoms, and their treatment.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1542,213,'level4',7,'Identify at least fifteen breeds of dog.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1543,213,'level4',8,'Learn how to properly groom a dog. Know how to trim their nails, clean their scent glands, and check their ears and fur. Know how to prevent fleas and ticks, or how to get rid of them if your dog has them.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1544,213,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1545,214,'preschool',0,'Learn what dog training is and why it’s important.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1546,214,'preschool',1,'With the help of an adult, teach your dog at least one simple command, such as sit, stay, roll over, come, fetch, etc. If you don’t have a dog, describe to an adult how you might teach a dog a command, and what command you would teach.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1547,214,'level1',2,'Read a book or have a book read to you on dog training.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1548,214,'level2',3,'Teach your dog at least two simple commands.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1549,214,'level2',4,'Research at least ten different dog training methods or commands. Make a list and attempt to teach your dog one of these methods/commands (it should be different from the commands you are teaching your dog in requirement 1).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1550,214,'level3',5,'Teach your dog at least three simple commands.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1551,214,'level3',6,'Learn about how to use dog treats properly during training. Find out which ones work best for your dog. Learn about the proper timing of treats. Practice having your dog obey commands for less and less treats, or sitting for longer periods of time before being rewarded.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1552,214,'level4',7,'Teach your dog at least four simple commands.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1553,214,'level4',8,'Find out what motivates your dog. Do you need to change it from time to time? Is it food, a toy, something from you (“rough house,” belly rub, etc?) Try different methods, keep notes and observe your dog as your training and rewarding him. Keep records of what works best for your dog.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1554,214,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1555,215,'preschool',0,'Find an example of a manufactured baby doll, a fashion doll, a souvenir doll, and a traditional doll from another culture. If you don’t know someone with all these types of dolls, look at a store or museum.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1556,215,'preschool',1,'Make something for your doll or a friend’s doll — a garment, a bouquet, a toy, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1557,215,'level1',2,'Choose two of the following: Save up your money to buy a new doll for someone who doesn’t have any, or to donate to charity or a children’s hospital. Make your own doll from fabric or purchased parts. A kit that has everything is fine. Host a tea party for at least one friend and his/her doll(s). Make an invitation to give your friend(s). You will need to decide whether to have real food and drinks or pretend ones. You need to help with cleaning up beforehand and afterwards. Go to some thrift stores or rummage sales and look for items that are a miniature version of the normal. See how many things you can find that would work with dolls even if they weren’t originally intended for dolls. Make a list to show your friends or another group, or if you are allowed to buy the items, show the items to your friends or other group. In this way, doll play encourages recycling.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1558,215,'level2',3,'Learn about the history of dolls. If your family collects old dolls, you can make a presentation to your family, friends, or group about the dolls you have. At least one doll should be over fifty years old. Be sure to show your friends what has changed in the way dolls are made. If your family doesn’t have a lot of old dolls, you will need to read from at least two sources about doll history or visit a doll display or museum that has antique dolls.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1559,215,'level3',4,'Learn about dolls from different cultures. Pick three cultures and find examples online or in books about what their dolls looks like. How are they different from American made dolls? What differences do you notice in clothing, accessories, facial features, hair, etc?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1560,215,'level4',5,'Make a list of things that are good about dolls and a list of ways in which one should guard against misuse. For your list of good things about dolls, find a picture, anecdote or story to go with half of the items on your list. Examples of good things would be that dolls can foster the imagination or bring comfort to a sick child. Misuse of dolls would include your dolls collecting dust. Discuss the differences of opinion about fashion dolls that have a lot of makeup, immodest clothing, or unrealistic proportions.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1561,215,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1567,218,'preschool',0,'What does “drama” mean? Talk about some examples of drama that you have seen.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1568,218,'level1',1,'What is the difference between main characters, supporting characters, and extras? Read a short play and explain what type of character each person is.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1569,218,'level1',2,'Dress Up – Using a variety of dress up items (hats, scarves, dresses, sunglasses, etc.) create a character and decide how that character would talk, walk, act, etc. Show your character to your family, friends, or group and see if they can guess what type of person you are.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1570,218,'level2',3,'Watch your favorite TV program and write down who the main characters are, who the supporting characters are, and who the extras are. Do the same for your favorite movie.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1571,218,'level2',4,'Expressing Emotion – Learn how to speak with prosody. Say the word “please” using a variety of emotions. Try saying it sweetly, impatiently, with a whine, excitedly, or with anger. How many emotions can you convey by only using this one word? Notice what body language accompanies how you express each emotion.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1572,218,'level3',5,'Why is expressing emotion important when performing a drama?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1573,218,'level3',6,'Research the history of theater. Prepare a timeline of how theater has evolved.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1574,218,'level4',7,'How do we use drama in our culture? Can it play a part in religious ceremonies? Politics? Education? Entertainment? Make a poster or booklet showing different ways that drama is used everyday.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1575,218,'level4',8,'Attend a play or theatrical performance and write a review. If you cannot get to a play, watch a production on any type of media (with parent’s permission) and write a review of what you watch.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1576,218,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1577,219,'preschool',0,'Make an original pencil, ink, crayon, charcoal, or chalk drawing.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1578,219,'preschool',1,'Choose any subject and draw it. Draw it again two more times. Compare your drawings. What changed? Did your drawing improve with practice? What else did you notice?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1579,219,'level1',2,'Look at least 10 different drawings in at least 3 styles. These can be cartoons, line drawings, value drawings, sketches, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1580,219,'level2',3,'Make two drawings using at least two different mediums.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1581,219,'level2',4,'Learn the following drawing terms and be able to show examples of each as well as explain why they are important to a good drawing. Focal point Composition Foreground Middleground Background Perspective');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1582,219,'level3',5,'Do at least 3 drawings using 3 different mediums.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1583,219,'level3',6,'Learn the following drawing terms and be able to show examples of each as well as explain why they are important to a good drawing. Overlapping Negative space Lines Balance Contrast Proportion');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1584,219,'level4',7,'Draw 4 pictures using 4 different mediums.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1585,219,'level4',8,'Read a book about drawing and try some of the techniques you learned about.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1586,219,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1587,220,'preschool',0,'There are many different types of drinks. Try at least three that you have never tried before.  Examples might include: Herbal teas Fruit smoothies Milkshakes and other ice cream based drinks Juices Hot chocolate Milk and milk substitutes Hot cider');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1588,220,'level1',1,'Choose three types of drinks and see how many different varieties you can find (For example, if you choose water, there is flat, sparkling, carbonated, tap, bottled, flavored, etc. If you choose milk, there is almond, coconut, soy, etc.). Taste at least three different varieties of your chosen drink. Which did you like best and why?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1589,220,'level2',2,'Learn the history of at least three different types of drinks.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1590,220,'level3',3,'Compare different brands of the same type of drink. For example, you might choose cola and compare Coca Cola, Pepsi, RC Cola, generic brands of cola, etc. How does the taste of each differ? What are the cost differences? As an alternative, you may compare several varieties of the same brand such as comparing Pepsi, Pepsi Throwback, Pepsi Max, Diet Pepsi, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1591,220,'level4',4,'Research drinks that have health benefits such as Kombucha. Alternately, research the health disadvantages of drinking sugary drinks or drinks sweetened with artificial sweeteners.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1592,220,'level5',5,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1595,222,'preschool',0,'Know what a drone is. How do they differ from other aircraft like airplanes and helicopters?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1596,222,'preschool',1,'Look at pictures and videos of several different types of drones.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1597,222,'level1',2,'Identify and describe 4 different types of drones, such as fixed-wing, quadcopters, hexacopters, and octocopters.  Discuss how they got their names and the pros and cons of each.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1598,222,'level2',3,'Learn about at least 3 different types of drone pilots (hobbyists, commercial, military, fire fighting, etc.) and the skills required for each.  What types of drones do they use?  What is the purpose of using a drone for what they do?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1599,222,'level3',4,'Create a timeline of drone history including at least 15 events.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1600,222,'level4',5,'Learn about the various sensors commonly used in drones, such as GPS, accelerometers, gyroscopes, barometers, and obstacle avoidance sensors.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1601,222,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1602,224,'preschool',0,'Identify three different types of ducks.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1603,224,'preschool',1,'Learn how to use a duck call.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1604,224,'level1',2,'Know how to tell a male duck from a female and be able to identify all major parts of a duck’s anatomy.  Know what baby ducks are called.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1605,224,'level2',3,'Visit someone who raises ducks and learn about their day-to-day care. If you cannot actually visit such a place, visit a virtual duck farm online with permission from your parents.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1606,224,'level3',4,'Find out how to hatch a duck egg. What temperature should the incubator be kept at? How long does the egg take to hatch? How often must they be turned?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1607,224,'level4',5,'Find out what the minimum amount of space is required to house ducks. Look at various coop designs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1608,224,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead. Optional Requirements');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1609,225,'preschool',0,'Find out what duct tape is. What makes it different than other tapes?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1610,225,'level1',1,'Do Preschool 1. When and why was duct tape created? Who created it?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1611,225,'level1',2,'What makes duct tape different from other tapes? What are other tapes used for? Look at at least five different types of tape.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1612,225,'level2',3,'How is duct tape manufactured? What is it made from?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1613,225,'level3',4,'A common saying is, “If it’s broken and needs fixing, use duct tape.” Learn about at least three different ways duct tape should NOT be used. What should you use instead?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1614,225,'level4',5,'Use duct tape to recycle or repair something instead of throwing it away.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1615,225,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1616,226,'preschool',0,'What day is Earth Day? Why is this an important holiday? Discuss it with a parent, friend, or other person.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1617,226,'preschool',1,'Find out what community events may take place around you. How do people participate in this day?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1618,226,'level1',2,'Learn about the history of Earth Day. Where is it celebrated in the world, and when? How did it begin? Why? Tell a group of your choice what you have learned.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1619,226,'level2',3,'Make an up-cycled craft and share it with your family, friends, or group. You can use old cans, cardboard, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1620,226,'level3',4,'Participate in an Earth Day event in your community.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1621,226,'level4',5,'Plan or help plan an Earth Day event for your troop. This could be a community service project, volunteering at the animal shelter, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1622,226,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1623,227,'level5',0,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead. Optional Requirements');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1624,228,'preschool',0,'What is edible art? Be able to name three different foods that can be made into art and make something out of at least one.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1625,228,'preschool',1,'Find at least three different pictures of edible art.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1626,228,'level1',2,'Make some edible flowers or animals to be used for decoration. These can be made out of marshmallows, candy, fruit roll ups, radishes, fruit, cookies, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1627,228,'level1',3,'Create a piece of edible art for a healthy snack, such as apple butterfly, cracker house, celery race car, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1628,228,'level2',4,'Find pictures of examples of professional edible art. These might be cakes, candy sculptures, or fruit carvings. How do people use edible art for events, table decor, etc.?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1629,228,'level3',5,'Find out about a career that uses a form of edible art. What education do you need? What can you expect to get paid? What hours would you expect to work?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1630,228,'level3',6,'Create a model of something that is edible, such as a sugar cookie map of the US, or a jello model of a cell structure.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1631,228,'level4',7,'Create a carving out of a melon, apple, or other fruit.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1632,228,'level5',8,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead. Optional Requirements.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1635,230,'preschool',0,'Identify the eggs of three different birds. Name five animals that lay eggs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1636,230,'preschool',1,'Identify the white and yolk of an egg.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1637,230,'level1',2,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1638,230,'level1',3,'How are eggs sized? What size of eggs are used in most recipes? Look at examples of two or three different sizes and compare.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1639,230,'level2',4,'Learn to separate the white and yolk of an egg. What do you use each one for separately? What are some recipes that require separating eggs? Why are eggs important in baking? What temperature should eggs be when adding them to a recipe?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1640,230,'level3',5,'Do you need a rooster to get eggs? Why do people keep a rooster? Why wouldn’t they keep a rooster? Learn about the nutrition of eggs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1641,230,'level4',6,'Check out grocery store eggs and labels (cage free, omega 3, organic, etc). What do the labels mean?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1642,230,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1645,232,'preschool',0,'Understand what it means to vote, and what an election is. Understand that we vote to choose who we want to represent us in government and what local rules we want to live by (local sales tax rates; wet/dry county laws; etc).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1646,232,'preschool',1,'Many different jobs in America are elected such as sheriffs, judges, school board officials, mayors, and governors. Do you know any elected officials? Know the difference between a Governor and a President.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1647,232,'level1',2,'Understand how voting affects our everyday lives through laws, institutions, and services to the community. How does voting affect you personally? How is voting effective in your life?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1648,232,'level1',3,'Learn the following election related vocabulary words: Ballot Absentee ballot Debate Incumbent Governor President Nominate Term limits Veto Voter turnout');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1649,232,'level2',4,'Learn the following additional vocabulary words: Campaign Congress Constituent Deficit Entitlement Exit poll Front-runner Grass roots Line-item veto Mudslinging');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1650,232,'level2',5,'Learn about the two main political parties, Republicans and Democrats, and what they stand for.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1651,232,'level3',6,'Add the following vocabulary words to your list: Activist Appropriations Legislature Bipartisan Democracy Republic Majority Leader Minority Leader Partisan Propaganda Spin');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1652,232,'level3',7,'Understand the structure and duties of local, state and federal government.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1653,232,'level4',8,'Add the following vocabulary words to your list: Balanced budget Campaign spending limits Caucus Electoral vote GOP Gross Domestic Product (GDP) Lame duck Pork barrel Suffrage Soft money Hard money Gerrymandering');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1654,232,'level4',9,'Learn the history of voting rights in America and create a timeline of how they have evolved.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1655,232,'level5',10,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1656,233,'preschool',0,'Learn safety precautions when dealing with electricity. Understand that electric sockets and the appliances plugged into them can be dangerous. Demonstrate the right way to connect and disconnect an electrical appliance such as a hair dryer or a phone charger.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1657,233,'preschool',1,'Help an adult make an electric potato clock or similar science project involving electricity.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1658,233,'level1',2,'Learn about different ways that electricity is made such as burning coal, hydro electric, solar, and wind. What are the pros and cons of each?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1659,233,'level2',3,'What is the difference between alternating and direct current? Why is it important to know the difference? Using a simple diagram, define a parallel circuit and a series circuit.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1660,233,'level3',4,'What is meant by current, voltage and resistance? Explain how determine one when you know the other two using Ohm’s Law.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1661,233,'level4',5,'Define the following terms: Volt Ampere Watt Ohm Resistance Potential difference Rectifier Rheostat Conductor Ground Circuit Short circuit Current Insulator Battery Alternator Transformer AC/DC.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1662,233,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1663,234,'preschool',0,'Read (or be read) a picture book that features a neurodivergent character. Talk about what made the character special.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1664,234,'preschool',1,'Learn that every brain is different and that being different is okay. Talk about something that makes you unique.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1665,234,'level1',2,'Watch a TV show or video that introduces autism, ADHD, or other forms of neurodiversity. Talk about what you learned.  How do your expectations of people change when you know their brain works differently than yours?  How can you change how you relate to them to be a better friend?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1666,234,'level2',3,'Define the term “neurodiversity” and learn what it means to be neurodivergent vs. neurotypical.  Learn about at least three different neurodivergent conditions (e.g., Autism, ADHD, Dyslexia, Tourette Syndrome).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1667,234,'level3',4,'Learn about at least 3 famous people who were/are neurodivergent.  How has this affected their lives and their careers?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1668,234,'level4',5,'Study neurodivergent communication styles. Practice alternative forms of communication like AAC, writing, or drawing.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1669,234,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach children, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your newfound knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1670,235,'preschool',0,'Learn what embroidery is. Look at pictures of clothes with embroidery on them. Do any of your clothes have embroidery on them?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1671,235,'preschool',1,'Learn to do simple running stitch. Learn how to begin and fasten off your stitching with a double stitch so it will not come undone. You may do this with an adult’s help.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1672,235,'level1',2,'Do Preschool 1 & 2. Be able to sew a straight line. Make a sample of your sewing on a small rectangle of fabric (approx 6 inches by 8 inches) and begin making a booklet of stitches.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1673,235,'level1',3,'Learn how to do back-stitch and cross-stitch. Make samples of each and add them to your booklet of stitches.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1674,235,'level2',4,'Learn to do chain stitch, over-stitch, and lazy daisy stitch. Make samples of each and add them to your booklet of stitches. Embroider a design using these stitches, such as a bunch of flowers. Be able to make French knots as the centers of your flowers.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1675,235,'level2',5,'Learn about the history of embroidery.  Embroidery was a much prized art-form in earlier times; find pictures of famous works of embroidery from history.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1676,235,'level3',6,'Learn to do buttonhole stitch, stem stitch, satin stitch, blanket stitch, and sheaf stitch. Make samples of each and add them to your booklet of stitches.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1677,235,'level3',7,'Embroider something small, such as a small pillow, using at least eight different stitches (A pre-stamped design is fine). It must take at least two hours of work. Show it to your family or club.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1678,235,'level4',8,'Learn how to do three-sided stitch, Florentine stitch, long and short stitch and Holbein stitch.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1679,235,'level4',9,'Draw the design for your own embroidery project and do it. Decide which stitches you will be using for what.  It must include at least twelve different stitches and take at least four hours of work.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1680,235,'level5',10,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1681,236,'preschool',0,'Know how to react to natural emergencies that may occur where you live. What kind of events you should be prepared for depends a lot on where you live. Do you need to be prepared for earthquakes? Tornadoes? Floods? Hurricanes? Drought? Fire? Understand how to keep a cool head and what do during these types of emergencies.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1682,236,'preschool',1,'Make a family evacuation plan and practice it. Know the different ways to get out of your house and where you should meet when you do. Explain why you should not hide in an emergency.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1683,236,'level1',2,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1684,236,'level1',3,'Know how to dial 911 in an emergency using a regular phone and a cell phone. Be prepared for the types of questions you will be asked, such as the nature of the emergency, where you are located, etc. Practice role playing 911 calls with a parent or leader. Know your complete address and phone number, your parents first and last names, and the phone number of someone else you can call in an emergency if your parents cannot be reached, such as an aunt, grandma or family friend.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1685,236,'level2',4,'Understand PP-RR: Prevent emergencies from happening whenever possible. Prepare for emergencies in case they happen Respond appropriately in an emergency Recover from an emergency Be able to explain each step for at least 10 different types of emergencies such as house fire, wildfire, tornado, hurricane, earthquake, car crash, flash flood, water accident, violence in a public place, chemical spill, gas leak, etc.  Focus on emergencies that might happen in your home, town, or during troop/club activties.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1686,236,'level3',5,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1687,236,'level3',6,'If electricity is out, normal cooking methods may not be available and fresh food may be hard to find. Cook a meal for your family using only canned, dry, or packaged food and use an improvised cooking method such as a portable stove, campfire, BBQ, etc. instead of your normal kitchen appliances.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1688,236,'level4',7,'Develop and know how to use a communication plan to reach all troop/club members and parents with speed in an emergency. Know who your out-of-town emergency contact is, and why it is important to have one.  If you are not part of a troop/club your communication plan should be to reach family members and friends.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1689,236,'level5',8,'and 2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1690,236,'level5',9,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead. Optional Requirements');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1691,237,'preschool',0,'Know what an emergency is, and how and when to call 911.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1692,237,'level1',1,'and recognize and name the key parts of the uniform of your chosen service.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1693,237,'level1',2,'Tour the local department of the emergency service you are studying (fire station, police station, Flight for Life, Ambulance company, Search and Rescue squad, or Humane Society, etc.).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1694,237,'level2',3,'Send thank you cards to the workers at your emergency services station or department.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1695,237,'level3',4,'Find out what kind of schooling and training is required to work in your chosen profession. Level 3 – Do at least 7 requirements including the 2 starred');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1696,237,'level3',5,'Research the history of your chosen organization in your community and/or the US.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1697,237,'level5',6,'Do Eagle requirements 1 & 2');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1698,237,'level5',7,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone.   You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge.   If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1701,239,'preschool',0,'Go on a shape hunt in your home or another location. Identify everywhere that the following shapes are present: square, circle, triangle, rectangle.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1702,239,'preschool',1,'Using commonly-available building blocks, see how high you can build a structure without it falling over. Are there other materials available nearby that you could use to improve it?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1703,239,'level1',2,'Find out about the different types of engineering. Pick one and discover three things an engineer in that field does.  Examples include areas such as civil engineering, mechanical engineering, structural engineering, computer engineering, marine engineering, biomedical engineering, environmental engineering, and many more');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1704,239,'level2',3,'Examine a simple engineering drawing (blueprint). Create your own blueprint for using recycled materials to build a birdhouse. Consider what a good birdhouse needs before you begin.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1705,239,'level3',4,'Learn about the history of engineering and create a timeline of at least  20 significant engineering advancements.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1706,239,'level4',5,'Choose three engineering types and research three things they do, and the education, experience and training required to work in those fields.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1707,239,'level5',6,'Research and design an engineering solution that addresses a specific accessibility challenge, considering inclusivity and universal design principles. The design may be simple, such as building a wooden ramp over a set of stairs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1708,240,'preschool',0,'Participate in a fundraising event for your club or a charity, or help someone in your family with their business. What can you do to increase sales or donations?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1709,240,'preschool',1,'Create a pretend store and play with your friends. For example, you might take out all your stuffed animals and open a pretend pet store. What kind of jobs might need to get done in your store? For example, if you have  a pet store, you will need to feed and clean up after your animals. You will also need to have a cash register and take payments when someone wants to buy your pets. Take turns with your friend being either the business owner or the customer.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1710,240,'level1',2,'An entrepreneur is basically someone who owns their own business. Brainstorm a list of ideas for a business you could start.  Maybe you could sell lemonade, make and sell a craft item, or even start a leaf raking service. How many ideas can you come up with? Owning your own business can make you money, but can also lose you money. Understand what revenue, expenses, and profit mean. Know the values of a penny, nickel, dime, quarter, and dollar.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1711,240,'level1',3,'With the help of an adult, sell an item you made, or a service you can perform. Make sure to follow all federal/state/local laws in regards to child labor and sales. You could sell vegetables you grew in your garden, potholders you sewed, or offer to wash windows or rake leaves. You can sell to friends and neighbors, or with the help of an adult, sell items at a craft fair, through a consignment store, on even on websites (do not surf these sites without parental permission) such as Zazzle,  Etsy, or eBay. Know what your expenses were, your revenue, and your profit.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1712,240,'level2',4,'Understand time vs. money. How much is your time worth? What is the current minimum wage?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1713,240,'level2',5,'Learn about the difference between wholesale and retail. Find out what the sales tax is in your city/county/state. Know what type of sales are subject to sales tax and what is not.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1714,240,'level3',6,'Understand business ethics. Discuss with an adult issues a business might face such as their impact on the environment, how they treat their employees,  copyright laws, customer safety, etc. Discuss both the right and wrong ways a business might handle these issues. Why do you think some businesses do not do the right thing? What ethics issues do you face with the product or service you sell?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1715,240,'level4',7,'Contact the Small Business Bureau or Association in your area. Find out how to create a business plan for your business. What resources can the SBA offer you?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1716,240,'level5',8,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1717,241,'preschool',0,'Understand what an escape room is and why people find them fun.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1718,241,'preschool',1,'Participate in an escape room activity.  This might be helping with a physical escape room, an escape room in a box, an escape app, etc.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1719,241,'level1',2,'Do Preschool requirements #1 and #2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1720,241,'level2',3,'Do Level 1 requirements #1 and #2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1721,241,'level2',4,'What types of puzzles can you expect at an escape room?  What skills would be useful?  Practice doing 3 different puzzles you may find in an escape room.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1722,241,'level3',5,'Do Level 2 requirements #1 and #2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1723,241,'level3',6,'Complete any style of escape room (Escape room live game, escape room in a box, escape room app, make your own escape room).');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1724,241,'level4',7,'Do Level 3 requirements #1 and #2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1725,241,'level4',8,'Learn about the history of escape rooms.  Who is considered the founder of escape rooms?  Create a timeline with 10 events related to the history of escape rooms.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1726,241,'level5',9,'Do Level 4 requirements #1 and #2.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1727,241,'level5',10,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1728,242,'preschool',0,'Learn what etiquette means.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1729,242,'level1',1,'Learn basic manners when interacting with others, such as: Wait your turn and do not interrupt other people when they are speaking. No name calling. Even if it’s in “fun,” name calling hurts. Always greet someone when they come over to your house. Say, “Please” and “Thank you” often. It shows respect and appreciation. In addition, if you are thanked, then say, “You’re welcome”. Clean up after yourself. Whether at home or at a friend’s house, always pick up after yourself. Be a good sport. After playing a game (sports, cards, board game), whether you win or lose, be nice. If you win, do not gloat or show off, but be kind. If you lose, don’t sulk or get mad, but be a good sport and tell the others “good game” or speak well of them. Take compliments with the intent they were given. If someone praises you, be gracious and say, “thank you,” and avoid putting yourself down or pointing out flaws. Open doors for others. When going into buildings, allow elders to go first and open the door for them. When preceding others into a building, don’t let the door slam in the face of those behind, but hold the door until the person behind can grab it. If someone holds the door for you, then remember to say “thank you”. Respect differences. When people do things differently from your family because of a difference in their culture, ability, or religion, show them respect. Sometimes it can be very interesting to see how different families do different things. Families have their own traditions or rituals and it is important and has meaning for that family even if it does not to you.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1730,242,'level1',2,'Learn proper table manners, such as: Wash hands before eating. Sit up straight at the table with your feet in front of you. Place your napkin in your lap. Use it only to dab you face. Do not use it to blow your nose. Excuse yourself and go to the bathroom if you need to do this. Eat with a fork unless the food is meant to be eaten with fingers. Hold your fork, knife and spoon correctly. Never hold them in a fist. Do not chew with your mouth open, or take such a big bite that you have difficulty chewing. Eat slowly and do not gobble your food. Do not speak with your mouth full. Always say please and thank you. If you do not wish to eat something, simply say, no thank you. Never season your food before tasting it. This implies that the cook cannot season food properly. Do not pick anything out of your teeth, it’s gross. If it bothers you that bad, excuse yourself and go to the restroom to pick. When eating rolls, break off a piece of bread before buttering. Eating a whole piece of bread looks tacky. Don’t reach over someone’s plate for something, ask for the item to be passed to you. Don’t make any rude comments about any food being served. It will hurt someone’s feelings. If the meal is not buffet style, then wait until everyone is served before eating. It shows consideration.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1731,242,'level2',3,'Learn proper party/event etiquette, such as: Issue invitations at least two weeks in advance through the mail. If you receive an invitation, RSVP as quickly as possible to help your host in her planning. Greet your guests politely when they arrive and make sure to introduce people who may not know anyone. Offer hospitality equally and generously to all guests. Wear clothing suited to the occasion. Contribute to conversations without dominating them and refrain from insults or prying curiosity. Eat neatly and quietly. Accept gifts or favors with humility and gratitude. Acknowledge gifts or favors with prompt thank you notes. Avoid disturbing others with unnecessary noise.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1732,242,'level3',4,'Learn the proper etiquette for cellphones/tablets/smartphones/mobile devices in public and in private, such as: You should only take a call/answer a text while with another person if it is an emergency or something extremely important. Be sure to apologize to the other person when you take such a call/answer such a text. Keep your conversation brief, and if possible, share what the conversation was about so the other person doesn’t think you were talking about them. Unless it’s an emergency/very important situation, be courteous to the person you’re with and keep your phone put away. Always tell someone if they are on speaker phone, especially when there are other people around. Never use a cell phone when being helped by someone in a restaurant, store, bank, etc. If you’re on the phone in a checkout line, end your call. Never text abbreviations to an adult or to someone you don’t know very well. Texting short hand is only appropriate in certain situations, such as with friends who know what you mean by your abbreviations. Never discuss personal issues in public over a cell phone for your own privacy and for being courteous to others. Keep private conversations for private settings. Never yell into a cell phone. Keep your voice low and even to be considerate of those around you. How long should you wait to return a missed call/text? Is it appropriate to return a call with a text? If you can, stand at least ten feet away from another person while on your cell phone in public. It’s courteous and gives you a little bit more privacy to carry on your conversation. There are times you should never use a cell phone unless it’s an emergency. Never text/take calls in a movie theater, during a class, job interview, wedding, funeral, worship service, performance, or any other place in which an audience’s attention is fixed on a presentation or it’s discourteous to others to be on your phone. If you must use your phone, step out into the hall or outside before doing so. Avoid using an annoying or loud ringtone on your phone while in public. Never listen to music or watch videos on your phone without headphones in public places, and only listen to music/watch videos when you can do so courteously. Never text when any activity at hand is dangerous or needs your full attention. E.g. crossing the street, walking on the sidewalk, using any sort of power/hand tool, etc. Levels 4-5: Never text or take a call while driving. Doing so jeopardizes your safety as well as others’ safety. Even hands free phones in the car can take your attention away from the road. It is best to pull over before responding to a text/call. Never use even a silent text while in a lecture, class, or meeting. Doing so is very discourteous to the speaker and is a distraction to everyone else around you. If you must use your phone, it is courteous to notify the speaker ahead of time (if possible) that you have a very good reason to keep your phone handy, and if you need to use it, you’ll step into the hall or outside. Be very courteous when using the camera on your phone. Never take photos/videos of people without asking them first, and never upload anything of the sort online without their approval. Be sure you are following all laws when taking pictures of things in public. Always be polite and courteous when speaking to another person, especially over texting. It’s sometimes very hard to understand what is meant by a text. Never text anything you wouldn’t say to them in real life, and refrain from texting when you’re upset.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1733,242,'level4',5,'Learn to perform polite introductions. Introducing people is one of the most common acts in life, yet few people know how to do it. Introduce a younger person to an older person; introduce a non-official person to an official person; and in business introduce the junior to the senior. Be sure to explain who people are and use their full names. Also do not assume that everyone wants to be called by his or her first name — wait until you are told to use a first name.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1734,242,'level5',6,'Teach someone how to do a skill from this badge or teach some knowledge about this badge to someone. You can teach kids, your spouse, seniors, anyone, just as long as you are sharing your new found knowledge. If for some reason you cannot teach what you have learned to someone else, you may choose an additional 2 optional requirements instead.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1735,243,'preschool',0,'Plan an event such as a troop ceremony, birthday party, dance, or large fundraiser. Preschool – Level 1: Help plan an event for at least 10 people. Level 2:  Plan for 20 people (if possible). Levels 3 – 5: Plan for at least 50 people (if possible). Set dates and times.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1736,243,'preschool',1,'Discuss what your budget will be. How much do you have to spend? How much will be allocated to food? Decor? Entertainment? Location rentals? Postage for invitations? Preschool – Level 1: Demonstrate a simple understanding of how a budget works. Levels 2-5: Create a detailed budget and stick to it.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1737,243,'preschool',2,'Choose a theme for your event and decide on appropriate decor. Will you purchase the decor? Make it? Borrow it?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1738,243,'preschool',3,'Plan food for your event. Will full meals be needed or just snacks? Are there any special dietary requirements of your guests? What type of place settings will you use? Paper and plastic? Good china? How will your food stay hot/cold?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1739,243,'preschool',4,'Where will your event be held? Can it hold enough people? Do you have enough seating?  Will you need to pay to rent the facility? Do you have to have insurance?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1740,243,'preschool',5,'Create a guest list and send out invitations at least three weeks prior to the event. Make sure to track the R.S.V.P.s so that you know how many people to expect. If this is a public event, how will you market it and get the word out?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1741,243,'preschool',6,'Do you plan to have entertainment? If so, what? Who will provide it? Will it cost money?  Do they require a deposit?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1742,243,'preschool',7,'Who will do the set up and clean up? How much time will it take? Are there items that need to be returned to other locations when you are done? Do you have enough cars to carry it all?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1743,243,'preschool',8,'Create a checklist you can use to make sure that everything from the previous requirements gets done. Include the date each checkpoint should be completed by as well as a supplies list to make sure nothing is forgotten. Don’t forget phone calls that have to be made, decorations that have to be made, and food that has to be made. If more than one person is helping to plan the event, make sure to list who is responsible for which jobs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1744,243,'level1',9,'Plan an event such as a troop ceremony, birthday party, dance, or large fundraiser. Preschool – Level 1: Help plan an event for at least 10 people. Level 2:  Plan for 20 people (if possible). Levels 3 – 5: Plan for at least 50 people (if possible). Set dates and times.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1745,243,'level1',10,'Discuss what your budget will be. How much do you have to spend? How much will be allocated to food? Decor? Entertainment? Location rentals? Postage for invitations? Preschool – Level 1: Demonstrate a simple understanding of how a budget works. Levels 2-5: Create a detailed budget and stick to it.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1746,243,'level1',11,'Choose a theme for your event and decide on appropriate decor. Will you purchase the decor? Make it? Borrow it?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1747,243,'level1',12,'Plan food for your event. Will full meals be needed or just snacks? Are there any special dietary requirements of your guests? What type of place settings will you use? Paper and plastic? Good china? How will your food stay hot/cold?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1748,243,'level1',13,'Where will your event be held? Can it hold enough people? Do you have enough seating?  Will you need to pay to rent the facility? Do you have to have insurance?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1749,243,'level1',14,'Create a guest list and send out invitations at least three weeks prior to the event. Make sure to track the R.S.V.P.s so that you know how many people to expect. If this is a public event, how will you market it and get the word out?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1750,243,'level1',15,'Do you plan to have entertainment? If so, what? Who will provide it? Will it cost money?  Do they require a deposit?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1751,243,'level1',16,'Who will do the set up and clean up? How much time will it take? Are there items that need to be returned to other locations when you are done? Do you have enough cars to carry it all?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1752,243,'level1',17,'Create a checklist you can use to make sure that everything from the previous requirements gets done. Include the date each checkpoint should be completed by as well as a supplies list to make sure nothing is forgotten. Don’t forget phone calls that have to be made, decorations that have to be made, and food that has to be made. If more than one person is helping to plan the event, make sure to list who is responsible for which jobs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1753,243,'level2',18,'Plan an event such as a troop ceremony, birthday party, dance, or large fundraiser. Preschool – Level 1: Help plan an event for at least 10 people. Level 2:  Plan for 20 people (if possible). Levels 3 – 5: Plan for at least 50 people (if possible). Set dates and times.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1754,243,'level2',19,'Discuss what your budget will be. How much do you have to spend? How much will be allocated to food? Decor? Entertainment? Location rentals? Postage for invitations? Preschool – Level 1: Demonstrate a simple understanding of how a budget works. Levels 2-5: Create a detailed budget and stick to it.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1755,243,'level2',20,'Choose a theme for your event and decide on appropriate decor. Will you purchase the decor? Make it? Borrow it?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1756,243,'level2',21,'Plan food for your event. Will full meals be needed or just snacks? Are there any special dietary requirements of your guests? What type of place settings will you use? Paper and plastic? Good china? How will your food stay hot/cold?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1757,243,'level2',22,'Where will your event be held? Can it hold enough people? Do you have enough seating?  Will you need to pay to rent the facility? Do you have to have insurance?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1758,243,'level2',23,'Create a guest list and send out invitations at least three weeks prior to the event. Make sure to track the R.S.V.P.s so that you know how many people to expect. If this is a public event, how will you market it and get the word out?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1759,243,'level2',24,'Do you plan to have entertainment? If so, what? Who will provide it? Will it cost money?  Do they require a deposit?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1760,243,'level2',25,'Who will do the set up and clean up? How much time will it take? Are there items that need to be returned to other locations when you are done? Do you have enough cars to carry it all?');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1761,243,'level2',26,'Create a checklist you can use to make sure that everything from the previous requirements gets done. Include the date each checkpoint should be completed by as well as a supplies list to make sure nothing is forgotten. Don’t forget phone calls that have to be made, decorations that have to be made, and food that has to be made. If more than one person is helping to plan the event, make sure to list who is responsible for which jobs.');
INSERT INTO badge_level_requirements VALUES(1762,243,'level3',27,'Plan an event such as a troop ceremony, birthday party, dance, or large fundraiser. Preschool – Level 1: Help plan an event for at least 10 people. Level 2:  Plan for 20 people (if possible). Levels 3 – 5: Plan for at least 50 people (if possible). Set dates and times.');
